title: 20 minute apple butter
directions: Cook until it comes to a boil; stir constantly.
Boil for 20 minutes and seal in jars.

title: taco dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese in glass 11 x 7-inch pan for 1 minute or until soft enough to spread.
Spread cheese across bottom of pan.
Pour chili on top.
Top with both cheeses.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: green devil cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add melted chocolate, sour cream or buttermilk, tomatoes, butter, eggs and grated orange peel. Beat with electric mixer on low speed until blended. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center removes clean. Cool on a wire rack. Remove from pans and frost when completely cool. Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
May be sprinkled with brown sugar.
Serve warm or cold with ham.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine; mix until smooth. Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Spoon chicken mixture onto triangles.
Pull corners to top and seal.
Brush with butter. Sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Use chicken soup as sauce when served.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender (about 10 minutes). Drain.
Cook carrots and onions in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup, sour cream, drained zucchini and 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter; add 3/4 cup stuffing and toss. Place on top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green rice
directions: In butter, saute onions and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Grate cheese over top if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is great with turkey!

title: marvel's mexican fiesta
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make Spanish rice according to box directions, using Mexican stewed tomatoes instead of plain stewed tomatoes.
Boil chicken; when cooked, shred meat.
Place Spanish rice over beans; spread shredded chicken over rice.
Cover with taco cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: pear preserves
directions: Cook everything until thick as honey, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: home canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir dry ingredients together and add half to mixture.
Beat bananas and add water to mixture.
Add vanilla and last of flour.
Add chopped dates and nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Watch!

title: calico casserole
directions: Mix together vegetables, stuffing mix, celery, onion, melted margarine, mayonnaise and half of the cheese.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fettucine with zucchini
directions: Trim the ends of zucchini and slice them into julienne strips. Cut the peppers into strips.
Heat olive oil in a skillet and saute the onions, garlic, zucchini and peppers for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the tomatoes, salt and dried red peppers and cook over very low heat for another 5 to 10 minutes. Drain and pour sauce over hot pasta.

title: president's brunch casserole
directions: Using Deerburger For Spaghetti Sauce: Add 2 beef bouillon cubes. Add fennel, garlic powder, spaghetti sauce packaged mix, thyme, oregano, basil and marjoram.

title: caramelized bacon
directions: Cut bacon in thirds.
Cover bacon with brown sugar, both sides.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Cover baking rack with foil. Cut slits in foil so the grease can fall through.
Place individual strips of bacon on the rack.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Watch closely!
These turn from done to burnt quickly, but are worth the effort.
Place individual strips on wax paper to cool.
Seal in a plastic container.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fried fish
directions: Dip fish fillets into lemon juice. Roll into batter (cornmeal, lemon pepper, onion, pepper and salt). Deep-fry in peanut oil. Wait until fish floats, then wait one minute more before removing.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; beat in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Put in 8 or 9-inch pan and sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon; dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrots and onions lorraine
directions: Clean carrots and slice thin.
Cook until tender.
Chop onion fine; brown lightly in butter.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to onion; mix well.
Pour onion mixture over cooked carrots; bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place all ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven or kettle. Cover and bring to a boil. Skim fat. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until the chicken is tender. Make dumplings as directed on recipe. I use parsley dumplings.

title: martin's minestrone
directions: In a stock pot, heat oil. Add sliced sausage and brown. Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil & cook for 8 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients except for white beans. Bring to boil, then cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans (with liquid) then simmer an additional 20-30 minutes.
Serve hot with warmed sliced Italian bread.

title: red beans and rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in large skillet.
Add ground sausage and brown.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375° with Minute rice.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° with cooked rice.
"I drain with cooked rice.
I don't drain with Minute rice."

title: pea salad
directions: Chop lettuce.
Add in carrots and onions.
Sprinkle sugar over lettuce.
Pour peas over lettuce.
Cover with Miracle Whip and top with shredded cheese and bacon bits.
Toss before serving.

title: mom's shrimp salad
directions: Cut shrimp in small pieces.
Drain corn and add chopped ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip and mix.
Use just enough to moisten.
tags: whole kernel vacuum packed Niblets corn

title: broccoli  rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in 8 x 8 casserole.	Bake for 35 minutes.

title: quick italian bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in peas and Italian seasoning.
Spread in plate.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs with fork until blended. Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer or until melted.

title: only the best hush puppies
directions: Cook corn meal in water over medium heat for approximately 6 minutes, stirring until batter becomes stiff and begins to roll into a ball.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, oil and onion. Gradually stir batter into beaten eggs (in a large bowl).
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Blend into corn meal batter.

title: smother chicken with potatoes
directions: Brown chicken in oil; drain grease to 3 tablespoons.
Add potatoes, cut into quarters.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are cooked.

title: chicken rice
directions: Mix soup and water together.
Put enough of the soup mixture to cover the bottom of the baking dish or casserole dish.
Mix in the rice.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour the rest of the soup mixture over.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours, or until done.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening until smooth.
Add eggs and sugar. Sift dry ingredients together and add, alternating with the milk. Add flavoring; beat until smooth.
Pour into a well-greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: honey coated mix
directions: Melt butter.
Combine butter and honey; coat everything. Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring every minute.

title: apple relish
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients thoroughly.
Add pickling spice in small cloth and boil until juice is thick.
Place it in jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: no bake fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine sugar and all remaining ingredients. Spray pan with Pam.
Pour mixture in pan.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: sweet spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, but not stiff.
Add sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken burritos
directions: In a skillet, cook pecans and onions in butter until onion is tender and pecans are lightly toasted.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, combine softened cream cheese, milk, salt and ground cumin. Add nut mixture and chopped, cooked chicken.
Stir together until well combined.
Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla shell; place near edge and roll up.
Place filled tortillas, seam down, in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: clam casserole
directions: Combine milk and crackers.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Spinach may be substituted for seafood.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put
potatoes
and
onions in casserole dish.
Then add the butter.
Mix sour cream, Cheez Whiz and soup in a separate bowl. After
the	sour cream, soup and cheese have been mixed together, pour
on top of potatoes.
Mash corn flakes and put on top.
Pour 3/4 cup butter over corn flakes and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: russian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter or margarine.
Add 1/4 cup water. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until done.
Put in covered casserole in oven to keep warm.
In skillet, cook mushrooms, onions, tomato and thyme in drippings for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and cook 1 minute more.
Dissolve the MBT in the remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add to skillet and cook until smooth. Remove from heat and add the sour cream.
Cook over very low heat about 3 minutes or until hot.
Pour over chicken and noodles or rice.

title: oriental beef
directions: Sprinkle the sliced beef with the marinade and allow it to marinate a half-hour or so.
Saute the beef and mushrooms in oil until mushrooms are soft and beef has lost its pink color.
Add onions and saute briefly.
Add chestnuts, peas, ginger and salt. Stir to combine.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and some of the beef broth.
Mix well.
Add to the meat mixture, then add the remaining broth and stir carefully as it heats and thickens. Transfer the mixture to a serving dish.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve with rice.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a very large pot, add beef and beef cubes to one half pot of water.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add water as needed.
When meat is tender, add onions, celery, carrots and tomatoes.
Cook 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.
After 1 hour, add tomato juice, potatoes and rest of vegetables.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Feeds a large family.

title: zesty cheese bake
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring all the time.
Cook until mixture thickens. Add pimentos, cayenne, salt and cheese.
Mix cooked rice with cheese sauce.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are browned.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken with orange sauce
directions: Brown chicken lightly on each side.
Place in baking dish. Pour the sauce over the chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on steamed rice topped with slivered almonds.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onions.
Add soup and thin with the water. Add tuna (drained) and noodles (drained).
Place in casserole.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apricot-oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour, oats,
sugar
and
soda in a large bowl; blend well.
Add	butter	and
vanilla;
mix
until
crumbly. Reserve 1 cup
of
the mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture into a greased
x 9-inch pan.	Spread apricot preserves on crust to within
inch
from
edge
of pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture and coconut.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers and onion very thin.
Put other ingredients in covered jar; shake to mix.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let marinate for several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put ground beef and onion in skillet and cover with water. Cook until hamburger is done and onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until spaghetti sauce like.

title: mrs. field's cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour and oatmeal (put small amount into blender until it turns into a powder; mix first, then blend), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, chocolate bar and chopped nuts.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, make golf ball size cookies 2 inches apart and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix the dill, Ranch dressing and corn oil together.
Put crackers on a cookie sheet or in a bowl and pour the mixture over the crackers; mix well until crackers are all coated.
Lay crackers on a cookie sheet and cover coated crackers with wax paper; put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, put paper towels on top of crackers to drain more of the oil off.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add nectar.
Let cool until syrupy.
Add other ingredients except cream.
Fold in whipped cream.
Place in greased individual molds or 1 large mold.

title: banana strawberry salad
directions: Wash and cut strawberries into half or quarters.
Sprinkle bananas with few drops lemon juice.
Add strawberry glaze and chill.

title: hershey's syrup cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place in bottom of casserole dish; spread soup over meat and slice Velveeta over soup.
Spread Tater Tots over cheese and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Work in flour and salt until dough holds together.
Shape dough by teaspoonful into 1-inch ball.
Beat egg white.
Slightly dip each ball into egg white and roll in nuts. Place one inch apart on ungreased baking sheet; press thumbprint deeply into each.
Bake approximately 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet; cool and fill with jelly or icing.

title: 5 minute peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour in buttered 9-inch square pan.

title: vidalia deep dish
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan; add rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine potatoes with just enough water to cover and salt. Cook until tender; drain and cool completely.

title: 24 hour salad(from 1933 cookbook)
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
When cold, fold in whipping cream (whipped) and fruit mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mini reuben sandwiches
directions: Assemble sandwiches using all ingredients in order.
One squeeze of dressing per sandwich is sufficient.
After sandwiches are assembled, heat in microwave for about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes for a great late night snack or for that unexpected company.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, margarine, baking powder and eggs. Place in a greased 9-inch pan.
Layer peaches and sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon that have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit bowl salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Mix in pecans.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over pecans.
Mix and spread in a greased pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and diced water chestnuts.
Add box of leek soup mix.
Stir.
Add spinach and stir.

title: fudge nougats
directions: In a saucepan, bring the sugar, margarine and milk to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in the chocolate chips, flour, graham crackers, nuts and vanilla. Pour into well buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn five minutes.
Cut from cob; measure.
Peel onions. Remove seeds from peppers.
Chop and measure cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients with one cup of water.
Simmer 20 minutes; bring to boiling.
Pack, while boiling hot, into jars and seal at once.

title: white chili
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and cook.
Then add diced potatoes and diced onion:
cook until onion and potatoes are soft.
Add beans and cumin and heat.
When this is warm add half & half then rewarm. When this is very warm add the cheese slowly while stirring. (Mixture needs to be very hot before adding cheese or it will stick to the bottom.)
After cheese has melted, serve with a dollop of sour cream if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 ungreased loaf pans.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: mother's fudge batter pudding
directions: Mix oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt; add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 5 tablespoons cocoa, 1/4 teaspoon salt and boiling water. Turn into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Drop batter by spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange cloud
directions: Drain oranges and chop.
Mix with Cool Whip and slowly add dry jello.

title: persimmon pudding(heritage)
directions: Wash persimmons; press through colander and then mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup coconut, if desired, before cooking.

title: three flour braided bread
directions: Combine 2 1/4 cups white flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add warm water (120° to 130°).
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed in electric mixer.
Add 1 cup white flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Divide batter into 3 bowls.
In one make whole wheat dough by beating 2 tablespoons molasses and 1 1/4 cups whole wheat flour into 1/3 of the batter.
Make white dough by beating 1 1/4 cups white flour into 1/3 of batter.
Make rye dough by adding 2 tablespoons molasses, caraway seed, cocoa powder and 1 1/4 cups rye flour to 1/3 of batter.
Knead each dough until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowls; cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down; divide each dough in half. Roll each piece (6) into a 15-inch rope.

title: creamy ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice into thin slices to measure about 4 cups.
Cut ham into small pieces.
Arrange 1/2 potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole, then ham and rest of potatoes. Prepare sauce by heating butter in a saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Pour white cream sauce over the top.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin in a mixing bowl.
Set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands; roll into bite-sized balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini and black-eyed peas
directions: You will need a large frying pan or wok.

title: microwave potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and green beans as directed in the microwave, approximately 6 to 7 minutes.
No need to skin potatoes.
Cut into small bite sized pieces.
Remove from oven and add the dressing, plus ripe olives.
Can also garnish top, after mixing well, with several slices of tomato.
Delicious hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: annie's chicken surprise
directions: Peel and wash potatoes and cut into quarters.
Place potatoes and chicken in shallow baking pan.
Mix the remainder of ingredients and pour over chicken and potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Bake for 10 to 15 more minutes at 400°.

title: garden cheese soup
directions: In large soup pot cook celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil).
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apricot-nectar dressing
directions: Stir brown sugar into yogurt.
Add apricot nectar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Cover and store in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes 1 cup (sixteen 1-tablespoon servings).

title: pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, oleo and sugar until creamed.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until fluffy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to Crisco mixture alternately with milk beating well.
Mix in vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan after loosening sides.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Blend well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked or graham cracker crust.
Chill for approximately 2 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour in batter; bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fig loaf
directions: Chop figs in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Beat sugar and butter in a large bowl at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and soda and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Spread in pan and bake about 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes in pan then remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: straw hats(good to serve to a crowd)
directions: On individual plates, stack ingredients in order given in list.
Amount according to number of servings.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites. Blend well. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Place cake in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
In a separate bowl put next 6 ingredients together.
Add sugar and butter mix.
Fold into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool in oven.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Put spices in pieces of cheesecloth and make a little bag out of it by tieing it up with a string; let the string extend over the side of the pan.
Simmer for 2 or more hours.
When tea is brewed, discard bag.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Serve over deep fried chicken or pork chops dipped in egg and flour batter and deep fried.

title: stadium spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers and vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours before rolling out and cutting.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Simmer syrup and margarine in 10-inch skillet 2 minutes.
Add carrots.
Cook 10 minutes or until carrots are glazed, stirring frequently.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese and mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Roll in small balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream and sugar together. Add Cool Whip and pecans. Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together. Pour into crust and chill.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Return to pot.
Add water to cover hamburger and rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes on medium.

title: vegetable-bean stew
directions: Heat oil in large pan over medium heat.
Add onions, red and green peppers, coriander and cinnamon.
Cook until onion is soft. Stir in sweet potatoes and cook 2 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice, saffron and drained garbanzos.
Season with salt.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix in zucchini and cook another 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Heat large skillet.
Add oil and butter.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until almost transparent.
Add zucchini.
Cook until just wilted.
Add wine vinegar, mustard and seasonings.
Add cheeses (reserve some Parmesan cheese) and salt and pepper.
Beat eggs with flour.
Combine with the zucchini mixture and pour into shallow 2 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Top with the extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1/2 hour until set in center and brown on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: lite creamy yogurt dressing for salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.

title: grandma's applesauce bars
directions: Mix oil and water.
Add soda to applesauce and combine with sugar.
Add flour, salt, nuts, cinnamon, raisins and vanilla. Blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased and floured 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Serve warm or cold.
May be reheated.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix all
together
and	bake until firm in 325° to 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and milk alternating with dry ingredients.
Add orange peel and zucchini.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
If using a glass pan, bake at 325° or if using a metal pan, bake at 350°.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Mix everything but the tortillas.
Spread mixture on each tortilla and put another and keep layering it.
Cut in pie shaped slices to serve.

title: cabbage tamales
directions: Cut the core out of the cabbage and put it in a large pot. Cover with boiling water.
Place a tight-fitting lid and let it set.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Then add pie filling, pineapple and cold water.
Chill.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the egg and stir in milk.
In other bowl, sift flour. Add sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add this to milk mixture. Heat grease in electric skillet to 375°; turn once.
Let drain on paper towel and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Fold in nuts.
Add crumbs.
Mix all carefully and pour into greased 8-inch pie tin.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and put whipped cream on top.
Serves 8.

title: wedding punch
directions: Scoop 1/4 to 1/2 sherbet into punch bowl and fill with lemon-lime soda. Mash sherbet to melt in bowl. This will foam.

title: boolkoki
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, water, garlic, green onion and pepper in a large baking dish.
Add beef and onion to marinade and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Add sesame oil to marinated beef mix and mix well.
Cook on power 8 for 6 to 7 minutes or until meat loses its pink color.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips and milk, bring to a boil.
Boil gently 4 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallow and stir until melted.
Chill.
Brown coconut in melted butter, stir in nuts and cereal.
Spread 3 cups of the mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Cut ice cream into 12 slices, arrange 6 slices over cereal mixture-cover with half of the chocolate mixture then remaining ice cream slices.
Cover with remaining chocolate mixture.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Cover and put in freezer.
Take out 5 minutes before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat all but butter and chocolate.
Melt butter and chocolate. Add to mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into 18 x 11-inch Teflon pan (no holes; thin).
Bake at 350° until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, garlic salt and onion salt together as a thick dip. Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on cream cheese and cool before serving.

title: microwave honey glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, salt and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave at full power 7 to 8 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Let stand.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Microwave at full power 45 to 60 seconds or until clear, thick and bubbly, stirring once.
Drain carrots.
Pour glaze over and toss.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add pineapple (undrained) and blueberries.
Let congeal.
Cream the cream cheese. Mix in the sour cream and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on top of congealed salad.
Nuts may be sprinkled on over top.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the sugar and butter.
Add grated sweet potato and milk.
Beat well.
Add ginger and orange rind. Place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake until golden brown.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in flour and beat until it becomes stiff.
Add berries carefully and, with fingertips, press into a 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain.
Add Velveeta cheese to melt.
When melted, remove from heat and spread on party rye. Freeze on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove from freezer and place in Ziploc bags.
Place in freezer for future use.
Heat in oven before serving.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets if necessary (check cookie mix package).
Prepare cookie dough according to directions on package.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour the pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top and spread evenly.
Cut up butter; sprinkle with nuts.
Add coconut, if desired.

title: chili rellenos casserole ii
directions: Mix cheese and chilies in large bowl.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Beat eggs, milk and flour until well blended.
Pour evenly over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread thick coating of taco sauce over top.
Sprinkle chopped tomatoes over all; return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: perfection salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and vinegar.
Add chopped ingredients when partially set.

title: apple squares
directions: In large bowl, cut butter (room temperature) into dry cake mix; set aside 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon the pie filling over the cake mixture.
In small bowl, combine reserved cake mixture and coconut.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown. Cool slightly before cutting into bars or squares.
Great with ice cream.
Can also be made with other pie fillings, as peach, blueberry, etc.

title: pull apart coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Shake biscuit pieces in sugar mixture. Stack in pan on top of pecans.
Add enough sugar to remainder of sugar-cinnamon mixture to make one cup.
Add melted oleo and boil for 1 minute.
Pour evenly over biscuit pieces in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: crystal pickles(sweet)
directions: Let stand 5 to 10 days.
Wash and cut into sticks.
Cover with water with 2 heaping tablespoonfuls alum overnight.
In the morning, wash, drain and make the following syrup.

title: mexicalli pie
directions: Brown ground meat with onion.
Add corn, salsa sauce, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spray a 10-inch pie pan with cooking spray.
Put meat mixture in pan.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Blend the first 7 ingredients in a blender.
Cut up the vegetables and pour refrigerated and chilled dressing over.
Makes large amount to serve.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add beef broth and cooking sherry.
Cook everything (simmer) 30 minutes.

title: tangy marinated broccoli
directions: Remove and discard stalks and leaves of broccoli.
Separate flowerets, wash, drain and place in large shallow container.
Set aside.
Combine vinegar, sugar, dill, salt, garlic, pepper and oil.
Mix well and pour over broccoli.
Toss gently to coat. Chill at least 24 hours.
Toss several times. Garnish with lemon slices.
May be served in marinade or drained.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: congealed cherry salad(served at teacher's appreciation luncheon.)
directions: Dissolve jello into water; add pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Congeal in refrigerator.
When firm, add topping.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add Cheez Whiz.
I use my hand mixer to mix.
Add cottage cheese to jello and remaining ingredients.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Bring peaches to a boil; drain and spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: two chocolate, chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In a heavy saucepan, melt over low heat the chips with the condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours. Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off and cut into squares. Store at room temperature in airtight container.
Yields about 4 dozen pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup melted margarine and sugar and press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grilled zucchini
directions: Combine olive oil, garlic, and soy sauce in glass baking dish and mix well.
Add zucchini and let marinate.
Turn occasionally so both sides will be well coated.
Let stand while preparing grill to medium heat.
Cook until brown and tender; about 4 minutes each side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to plates and serve.

title: frosted ham ball
directions: Mix ham, raisins, onion, curry and mayonnaise.
Make into a ball.
Soften cream cheese with milk and ice the ball.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: virginia rebels(cookies)
directions: Cream butter with vanilla; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg, then alternately the sifted dry ingredients with water until well blended.
Add rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Makes about 15 dozen cookies.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: grandma grace crabtree's homemade buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to cooled milk.
Add potatoes, shortening, sugar or honey, salt and eggs.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Knead a little, not very much.
Shape into rolls; let rise.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: beer loaf cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Stir in eggs.
In another bowl, sift flour, spices, soda and salt.
Add flour and beer alternately to sugar mixture, starting and ending with flour.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: salsa bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
Combine beans, onion and pepper in large bowl.
In small bowl combine salsa, Italian dressing, sugar and salt.
Add to bean mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Stir in chopped tomato before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup and 1/2 can of onions in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: easy crunchy chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a big Ziploc bag.
Roll the bag with a rolling pin until crumbs are made.
Wet chicken pieces with water and shake in the bag.
Lay pieces in a casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: health drink
directions: Mix in blender.
Add ice and smaller amounts of water to blender for a slushie drink.

title: roast pork with creamy mushroom gravy
directions: Cut garlic into 1/8-inch slices; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Place roast, fat side up, on a greased rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Cut 1/2-inch slits
at 1-inch intervals in diagonal rows on top of roast; insert garlic slices deep into slits.
Brush lemon juice evenly over roast; sprinkle with pepper and remaining 1 1/4 teaspoons salt.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (30 minutes per pound) or until meat thermometer registers 160°. Transfer roast to a serving platter; let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve with Creamy Mushroom Gravy. Yield:
8 servings.

title: dip recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 2 pie shells for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Place margarine and marshmallows in a large saucepan and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix until coated with marshmallow mixture.
Using waxed paper spread mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: potato bread and donuts
directions: *For donuts, add 2 eggs and add more flour.

title: hearty breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine egg, milk, shortening and pancake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with sausage.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix eggs and sour cream, then add corn and corn bread mix. Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut pads of butter on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cinnamon candy(hard tack)
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard crack stage (300°). Remove from heat.
Add flavored oil and food coloring.
Pour onto cookie sheet that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
When cool, crack and sprinkle with more powdered sugar to prevent candy from sticking together.
Stir only until it boils.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chopped chicken, chopped eggs and all other ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with toasted bread crumbs.
Dot butter over crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio dream
directions: First layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Mix in sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla. Fold cream cheese mixture in pudding mixture.
Layer in pan with crushed Oreos on top of each layer.
Can use large bowl.

title: very rich ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 1 can milk until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add the other can of milk.
Add 2 cans water.
Mix well.
Add Eagle Brand.
Cook over low flame until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Set aside to cool. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Pour in freezer and freeze.

title: yeast pizza-sausage
directions: Brown sausage or hamburger in skillet and drain.
Mix oregano and tomato paste, then spread over prepared crust.
Top with sausage.
Cover with mixture of grated cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn; mix well.
Bake in a large roaster for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove and break.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Place 3 cups lettuce in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Place layer of sliced eggs, salt and pepper, then layer of peas, layer of lettuce, layer of bacon and layer of cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over all and seal to edge of bowl with mayonnaise. Cover and chill 24 hours.
Garnish with paprika.

title: grandma's turkey dressing
directions: Saute together onions and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Combine tomato ketchup and chili sauce in mixing bowl.
Stir in prepared horseradish.
Use 1 tablespoon of lemon juice and 2 or 3 dashes of Tabasco sauce.
If you desire more tartness or hot flavor, use remaining lemon juice and another dash or two of Tabasco sauce.
I usually use only 3 ounces of horseradish to start and then adjust the lemon juice and Tabasco to taste.

title: dirt pie
directions: *Use granola chunks, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, chopped peanuts or a combination.

title: easy berry dessert
directions: Cream butter.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; blend to make mixture crumbly.
Put berries on bottom of glass bowl or glass pan.
Add mixture.
Microwave for 10 to 12 minutes until bubbly all over.
Start by 5 minutes and check every 2 to 3 minute intervals so it does not overcook.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken (that has been cut into small strips) until browned. Remove. Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: soup mixture
directions: Mix.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour in jars and pressure at 10 pounds for 40 minutes. Makes 7 quarts.

title: hot taco salad
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz.
Chop Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies in blender for a couple of seconds.
Add tomatoes and green chilies to cheese and heat until bubbly.

title: curried chicken
directions: Combine soup and curry, onion and garlic powders; puree in blender.
Place in 1-quart saucepan; bring to boil.
Add chicken; simmer 5 minutes.
Add honey and raisins and cook 5 minutes longer. Serve over brown rice.

title: fish fritters
directions: Use large bass filets.	Boil in cajun crab shrimp seasoning till flakes apart.	Cool and mash up.
Add all ingredients and squish up.	Needs to be consistency to form into balls (slightly smaller than golf ball).
Drop fritters into 350° deep fryer.
Fry till golden brown.

title: apple walnut ring
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix and sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and mace.
Add gradually.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts. Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and remove to rack.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple; stir in Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Stir and let cool.
When it starts to thicken, add buttermilk.
Let set until thickened.
Then stir in Cool Whip. Pour into a dish and refrigerate.

title: date-coconut balls
directions: Mix together and cook over a very low heat, bring to boil and boil 2 minutes, be very careful not to scorch.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups of rice Krispies and 2 cups of chopped nuts (we like walnuts but you can use pecans).
Mix well.
Cool a few minutes so you can roll a large teaspoonful into balls.
Then roll in coconut.
Be sure to work fast enough so your coconut will stick to the balls. These can be frozen in a tight container for several weeks.
They will also keep well in a tight container just for eating.

title: dijon mustard marinade(for grilled flank steak or london broil)
directions: Whisk together ingredients, adding water last.
Place 3 1/2 to 4 pounds flank steak in large flat ceramic or glass dish.
Pour marinade on top to coat.
Then turn steak and coat other side. Prick with fork several times.
Refrigerate covered overnight or for 5 to 6 hours.
Grill steak and baste with marinade while grilling.
Slice thinly to serve.
Serves 8.

title: fruit and nut clusters
directions: Line some cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chips.
Stir in almonds, dates and cherries. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until set. Store in airtight container in a cool place.
Makes approximately 32 pieces.

title: dip
directions: Press softened cream cheese in dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and red pepper.
Cook sausage; drain and put on top of this.
Cook mushrooms in sausage grease (or butter) and put on top of sausage. Add the taco sauce, olives and cheese.
Heat thoroughly at 300°. Serve with taco chips, etc.

title: salmon log or ball
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones and flake.
With mixer, whip cream cheese.
Blend in lime juice, onion, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke and pepper.
Stir in salmon. Spread pecans and parsley on sheet of waxed paper.
Turn out mixture and roll until covered.
Chill.

title: laurine's refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
In large bowl, combine cool milk, eggs, sugar, butter, salt and yeast; mix well.
Mix in sifted flour, 1 cup at a time.
The dough should be a little on the soft side.
Knead quickly and lightly on a very lightly floured surface.
Shape into a smooth ball.
Place in a large buttered bowl.
Butter top; cover with a clean cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Grease your pan. Roll the rolls into small lemon size balls with your hands.
Butter tops again.
Cover; set in a warm place to rise until double in bulk.

title: broiled shrimp with garlic butter
directions: Shell the uncooked shrimp but do not remove the tails.
Split them down the back and remove the intestinal veins.
Wash under cold water and dry.
Preheat broiler to the highest temperature. In a pan melt the butter; then add the oil, lemon juice, scallions, garlic and pepper.
Add shrimp and broil 3 to 4 inches from the heat for 5 minutes.
Then turn and broil 5 minutes on the other side.
Serve on a platter with parsley and strained juices from the pan.

title: brownies
directions: Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne romana(prepare in advance)
directions: The day before serving or early same day saute onions in hot oil until light brown.
Add beef and cook until red color is lost! Mix garlic with salt.
Add pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Simmer, covered, 40 minutes.
Refrigerate until final preparation.

title: betty's fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275° to 300°.
Chop fruit and pecans.
(Chop fruit very small.)
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and milk. Reserve 1/2 cup flour.
Mix 2 1/2 cups flour with spices and soda. Add to creamed sugar and butter alternately with whiskey. Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour over the chopped fruit and nuts; add to cookie batter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon and bake for 20 minutes.
These will keep for a very long time.

title: strawberry jam with pectin(sugar-free)
directions: Crush strawberries in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in artificial sweetener, food coloring, powdered fruit pectin and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Continue to stir 2 minutes.
Pour into freezer containers.
Cover and freeze.
Thaw before serving.
Store in refrigerator after opening.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Heat milk; add marshmallows.
Stir ingredients until melted. Cool.
Fold raspberries, cream and nuts into marshmallow mixture and pour over crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: french rarebit
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise, and tear out some of the inside, leaving a shallow indentation.
Spread with butter, sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Slice cheese, layer on top.
Reserve peel and boil potatoes, about 20 minutes, add milk, butter and salad dressing to taste, mash.
Put bread in 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Heat creamed corn in saucepan over medium heat.
When bread is warm and cheese is melted, remove from oven.
Cover with mashed potatoes, spoon creamed corn liberally over all.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Bring to boil, then simmer until tender.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water until well blended.
Boil rapidly until the mixture spins 6 to 8-inch thread or reaches 240°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo with cream cheese until smooth; add sugar and beat until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour gradually; stir in vanilla.
Spoon into a tube pan and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and peel while hot.
Slice into a bowl, then add cut-up bacon that has been fried until crisp.
Dice onion and add into potatoes.
Mix oil, vinegar, water, pepper, salt, basil, parsley and sugar in a small bowl.
Then add into potatoes.
Stir thoroughly and serve.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Grind cranberries and peeled and seeded oranges.
Add sugar and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: garlic scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute garlic in butter in large pan.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, gradually blend in chicken broth until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add horseradish.
Arrange 1/3 of potatoes in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 of ham over potatoes.
Season to taste with paprika.
Pour over 1/3 of cream sauce.
Repeat layering, ending with potatoes.
Pour remaining cream sauce over.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and continue cooking until potatoes are tender and top is golden brown (about 1 hour).
Sprinkle a little parsley over top.
Serves 6.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Add all ingredients and chill for 4 hrs. and serve.

title: brown stew(andre)
directions: Thoroughly brown meat in fat. Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, sliced onion, bay leaves and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 2 hours. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking. Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes. Cover and continue cooking until vegetables are done.

title: cheese ravioli asparagus pie(casserole)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
In a bowl, slightly beat eggs; stir in soup and pepper.
Put ravioli in bottom of pan in a single layer, then spoon 1/2 of the mixture over them.
Top with 1/2 of zucchini, tomatoes, basil and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, then top with remaining 1/2 soup mixture, then another layer of tomatoes, zucchini, basil and Mozzarella.
Bake 45 minutes or until set in center and brown on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Stir in cold water, and cranberries.
Beat until smooth.
When partially set stir in marshmallows, apple and celery.
Chill until set.
Use a 9 x 13 dish.

title: pole vault pepper steak
directions: Mix dressing, sherry and ginger.
Pour over meat; cover. Refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream together butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pat out into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mama's day off casserole
directions: Flatten beef into bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over beef.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 55 minutes, or until the meat is done.
Cooking time may vary, depending on size and type of casserole.

title: grill cheese toast
directions: Put the slices of bread in toaster.
Put the cheese on 10 slices of toast.
Next, put the other 10 toast on top and put in the skillet of margarine.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes 1/2 cup margarine, egg and cake mix.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows over cake.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, cook margarine, peanut butter chips and white syrup until chips are melted.
Remove from burner and add Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Stir mixture together and spread over marshmallows. Press down lightly.
Cool and cut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water (should cover chicken).
Cool and remove meat from bone.
Place chicken in bottom of baking dish. Save 2 cups broth.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix broth from chicken with Stove Top stuffing.
Spoon this mixture on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and stuffing is lightly brown.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain, reserving the liquid (add enough water to make 1 cup).
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and horseradish until smooth.
Stir in shrimp and hot sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: indian fry bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat buttermilk until bubbles form at the edge.
Set aside and allow to cool, then stir in egg, oil, sugar and yeast until well blended.
Set aside 5 minutes.
In large bowl, stir together 5 cups of flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Make well in center of flour mixture.
Pour buttermilk mixture into well.
Stir until soft dough forms.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Place all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into baked pie shell or tarts.
Cool, chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes. Stir very well.
Microwave on High 4 more minutes, then stir in vanilla and margarine.
Microwave on High 2 more minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons of baking soda.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Let cool; break apart.

title: gramma's peanut brittle
directions: Must have a marble slab and candy thermometer.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute the sugar, water, vinegar and egg.
Let cool to room temperature.
Fold in the mayonnaise. Enough dressing for 4 to 6 potatoes.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Combine peas, mushrooms, bean sprouts and water chestnuts and put in 9-inch casserole.
Pour heated soup over vegetables.
Grate cheese over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove.
Put onion rings on top and put back in oven for 15 minutes longer, until brown.
Serve as a vegetable or you can add chicken, turkey, tuna or 1 pound of hamburger, browned.
Serve with hot buttered garlic bread.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil, drain and cool rice.
Add all ingredients and mix well. For added flavor, add some Lawry's seasoned salt.

title: no fat coleslaw
directions: Stir yogurt, vinegar and honey until smooth and well blended. Add vegetables and mix well.

title: chicken cashew
directions: In 1/2 cup water, boil celery and onion until soft.
Drain remaining water.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix crackers and milk until soft.
Add egg and corn.
Season. Bake in greased casserole dish for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. (Corn should be "set" almost like custard.)

title: karen's easy chicken
directions: Or use your own seasonings.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Place chicken pieces in a baking dish.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook gently for 5 minutes. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir and cook 5 minutes more.

title: arizona barbecue beef(freezes well)
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Add all ingredients except catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes per pound of meat.
Cool.
Remove fat and bone.
Pull meat apart into bite size shreds and chunks.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Reheat before serving on crisp buns.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pizza dogs
directions: Open bun.
Place hot dog in bun.
Pour 1/4 cup pizza sauce over hot dog. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese liberally over sauce. Cook in microwave on High approximately 1 to 1 1/2 minutes each.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken or fish in the ritz
directions: Roll enough Ritz crackers to make crumbs.
Dip parts in cracker crumbs, then in egg mixture.
Season with salt and pepper, then dip in crackers again.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: shrimp jalapeno mold
directions: Heat soup and melt cream cheese in the soup. Add gelatin and stir until melted into mixture. Add other ingredients and pour into a mold which has been coated with mayonnaise.

title: august cooler
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Freeze partially with mixer, whipped until smooth. Refreeze.

title: summer macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; rinse with cold water.
In a medium size bowl, combine macaroni, peas, cheese, pickles, onion, green peppers and pimento.
In a separate small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, heavy cream, salt and pepper.
Blend into macaroni mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: egg and caviar hors d'oeuvre
directions: Hard-boil eggs, peel, grate and mix with mayonnaise.
Spread in bottom of shallow dish.
Chop 1 1/2 cup purple onion and layer over egg mixture.
Blend 2/3 cup of sour cream with an 8 ounce package of softened cream cheese.
Using wet spatula, spread cream mixture over layer of purple onion.
Refrigerate.

title: grandmother's german apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with mixture of water, cinnamon and salt.
Work together until crumbly sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle on top of apples. Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.	Refrigerate.

title: tuna treat
directions: Cook noodles; drain and place in casserole dish.
Place tuna on top of noodles, then add peas.
Cover with warm broth.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple pie(9-inch)
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit salt.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and put in large, shallow casserole.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Freezes well.

title: weenies and sauce
directions: Add favorite barbecue sauce to hot dogs (enough to cover hot dogs).
Heat in oven until warm, about 20 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and set aside.
Brown beef and onion in heavy pan. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer.
Cover with cheese and melt.

title: cocktail sauce(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: good salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook for 45 minutes. Put in sterilized jars and seal at once. Place in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: french raisin toast
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in a wide shallow bowl.
Beat in eggs and milk,
Add bread; let stand to coat, then turn to coat other side.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Mix well.
Beat egg yolks, butter, milk and first mixture.
Cook until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches on top of stove.
Melt butter in bread pan in oven.
Pour heated peaches on top of butter in pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour on peaches and butter. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cinnamon streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 8-inch square or round pan with no-stick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine 2/3 cup cereal, flour, 1/2 cup sugar and baking powder; add 1/4 teaspoon salt if desired.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil, egg and vanilla; add to reserved cereal mixture all at once.
Stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan; set aside.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/3 cup cereal, remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over reserved cake batter; cut through batter with knife to swirl.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done. Serve with warm applesauce if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: coconut jam filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
With mixer, cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Beat in flour mixture, then oats.
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make depression in center of each; fill with jam.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.

title: marlene's lemon fluff
directions: Mix graham crackers, oleo and sugar. Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Fill a quart jar with cucumber and onion slices. Mix well all of the remaining ingredients and pour over slices. Seal jar. These will keep several weeks in the refrigerator. You may add more vegetables or use the mixture as a salad dressing.

title: tofu muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin tins.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture from blender over the dry ingredients and stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full and bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 10 muffins.
Serve with honey.

title: apple pie mix
directions: In a large kettle cook ingredients until thickens.
Pack apples into sterilized jars, then pour apple pie mix on top of apples; seal while hot.
Set jars of apple mix in a boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Put all ingredients into a closed container and shake well. Let it settle for at least 4 hours before using.
Works best with Joy or Dawn dish detergent.

title: hearty chicken stew(lo-fat)
directions: In a Dutch oven heat oil over medium heat.
Saute the onion, ginger and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add flour.
Cook 1 minute.
(Stir fast so it doesn't burn.)
Stir in tomatoes and cook 2 minutes. Wrap peppercorns, cloves and cinnamon stick in cheesecloth.
Add chicken, spice bag, water and Worcestershire sauce to onion mix. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add the vegetables and cook, covered, until all are tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Remove spices and serve hot.
The amount of chicken can vary and a suggestion would be to take a whole chicken, debone it and cut it into bite size before adding it to the pan.
Can be frozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: german pizza
directions: In a 12-inch stove-top skillet or electric skillet over medium heat, brown hamburger with
onion,
green
peppers, 1/2 teaspoon salt
and
pepper.
Melt
butter.
Spread
potatoes, (which have been peeled and finely
shredded)
over butter and sprinkle with remaining salt.
Top with meat mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cook,
covered,
until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; cover and heat until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Cut
into
wedges or squares to serve.

title: hungarian shortribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides.
Add onions and cook until tender. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ribs and cook until meat is tender (2 or 3
hours).
Slowly thicken gravy.
Serve over noodles.

title: green potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil in broth until very tender.
Cook sausage in skillet; drain and cut into slices. Mash or blend potatoes and broth.
Heat to boiling and add spinach and cook until wilted.
Add sausage, pepper and cream.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in stockpot; simmer together, covered, for 40 minutes.
Drain, saving all broth.
Put vegetables in
a blender and mix.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli and pare stems.
Separate flowerets.
Cut stems into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a kettle until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add curry powder, chicken broth, water and salt to kettle.
Bring to boil and add broccoli and potatoes.
Return to boiling.
Lower heat.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Puree mixture in blender and stir in half and half.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Remove to a shallow roasting pan.

title: squash squash
directions: Over medium heat, saute garlic and onion with squash until tender.
Add salt and pepper to flavor.

title: meatballs(6 dozen)
directions: Mix
the first 6 ingredients well.
Roll mixture into balls and brown in skillet thoroughly on all sides.
As they brown, mix separately in a saucepan two 14 ounce bottles of hot ketchup.
One should be Heinz hot ketchup and the other one Brooks tangy ketchup.
Add to this one small jar of apple jelly.
Simmer.
Add meatballs to the sauce and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place butter, potatoes, carrots, celery and parsley in 12 cup casserole.
Cover and microwave 8 minutes.
Add chicken breasts and anise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix in flour; pour in chicken stock, cover and microwave 6 minutes.
Stir in onions and microwave 2 minutes, uncovered.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots just until crisp-tender. Drain. Combine all remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.

Add carrots and stir until well mixed. Cover and refrigerate at least 3-4 hours. Serve cold as a salad or warm it and use as a side dish. Store in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. This is easy to make and can be prepared well ahead of time.

title: shrimp with apples and snow peas
directions: Drop cleaned snow peas into a pot of boiling water.
When tender, but still crunchy, after about 3 minutes, drain them and plunge immediately into ice water to stop cooking and set color. Reserve.

title: sandworks
directions: Visit the beach or river shore.
Find wet sand.
Explore and create.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain and put in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients. Cook for 1 hour on high or until heated thoroughly. When ready to serve, serve with the following toppings: sour cream, grated cheese, green onions, corn chips and diced tomatoes.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until slightly thickened.
(Use fork or whisk.)
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.

title: sour cream dill potato salad
directions: Combine sour cream, vinegar, salt, dill weed and pepper in small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add sour cream mixture and toss gently.
Chill, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 cup of the cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Cook macaroni as directed. Combine with sauce in a baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add last 2 ingredients.
Stir well.
Serve over buttered biscuits.

title: orange delight
directions: Crust:
Mix the first 6 ingredients; press into a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: deer hunter's pie
directions: Saute meat in a heavy skillet until lightly browned.
Arrange a layer of potatoes over bottom of a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish; follow with a layer of meat, a layer of onions and a layer of apples.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Heat the beef stock, nutmeg, pepper and salt.
Pour liquid mixture over casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: english trifle (strawberry)
directions: Make pudding; refrigerate.
Cut or tear cake into small pieces and wrap around the frozen strawberries in a large bowl or trifle bowl.
Pour orange juice on top of cake.
Sprinkle with desired amount of brandy.
Pour pudding mixture on top of cake mixture. Top with whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple whip cake
directions: Add eggs, applesauce and oranges with juice to cake mix.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake by directions on cake mix box.

title: fried artichoke fritters(fried noekkelost)
directions: Cut artichokes into quarters.
In small mixer bowl, beat cheeses with an electric mixer on medium speed until well combined. Mold about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture around each artichoke heart. Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix oleo, graham cracker crumbs and soda cracker crumbs.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Cook noodles and broccoli.
Layer beef, noodles, broccoli and cheese.
Pour soup over mixture and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: soft apple cider cookies
directions: In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add cider and eggbeaters, beat until smooth.
At low speed gradually blend flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Drop by spoonful 2 inches apart onto greased bakery sheet.
Bake 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from sheet.
Cool on wire rack.

title: blue cheese butter sauce
directions: Beat softened butter, Blue cheese and horseradish together. Top a hamburger or steak just before serving.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Heat shortening; add onions, celery, peppers, and tomato sauce. Cook over medium heat in uncovered pot until onions are wilted. Cover and cook 15 minutes. Add sausage and green onions; cook 30 minutes. Add rice and water; cover and simmer until rice is done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until creamy. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix oil, eggs, water, and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350 for 30-35 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar and cooking oil and heat until warm, not hot. Heat milk solution in pressure cooker pot.
Add yeast and let stand for about 10 minutes. Stir in flour and salt.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let stand for about an hour.
Knead and form into rolls.
The less flour you add while kneading, the better.
Let stand for another hour.
Then you can shape rolls and bake.

title: rocky road s'mores
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add graham cracker crumbs and flour and mix well.
Press into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: bubble bread
directions: Allow bread to raise.
Melt the butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together (you may need more).
Tear pieces of bread into balls about size of walnuts.
Dip into butter and roll into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Pour the remaining butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Slice tomatoes and fry in butter or oil just covering bottom of frying pan.
Add flour, stirring to absorb oil.
Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over potatoes, bread, biscuits, etc.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix biscuit mix according to package directions. Roll out thin, about 1/16 - inch. Spread sausage on biscuit dough. Roll up jelly roll style. Freeze about 2 hours. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Add onion, bell pepper, soup, sour cream, carrots, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle layer of crumbs in bottom.
Add squash and cover light layer of crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with beans.
Layer the ingredients, beginning with beans and ending with taco sauce.
Make first layer round on a serving plate.
Surround finished dip with natural corn chips.

title: impossible chicken tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix chicken, corn and seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate and sprinkle with chilies and cheese, then set aside.

title: nasty pudding
directions: Cook cake according to box directions in 2 cake pans.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes.
Slice layers in half with long knife. Alternate layers with icing in big bowl, beginning with a small amount of icing first.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry onion and ground beef in a bit of oil until brown.
Drain. Add drained green beans, tomato soup and tomato rice soup.
Heat until warm.
Pour warm mixture into rectangular casserole dish.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream well butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, and baking powder. Combine flour and egg mixtures.
Add oatmeal, rice krispies, and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: gallon chili sauce
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add paprika, pepper, salt, mustard and chili powder.
Stir into browned meat.
Add water and oil and stir.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours, then add enough flour to thicken to your likeness.
For a small amount, third the recipe.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, mix milk, oil and honey.
Gradually stir into yeast and water.
Add 4 cups flour and stir; beat for 3 minutes.
Add 4 more cups flour; beat until stiff.
Knead 12 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with cloth.
Let rise in a warm place (85°) for 40 to 60 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Cut in 3 equal parts; shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Cover; let rise for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Brush tops with oil or butter; cool a few minutes before turning out on cooling racks.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain well.
Add soup, chili and garlic powder.
In a casserole dish, put tortilla chips and half of the meat mixture and the cheese.
On top,
repeat chips, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted. Serve hot with chips, sour cream and salsa.

title: green chile stuffed chicken sandwiches
directions: Slice chicken breasts and place green chile strips in between. Marinate chicken breasts and chile strips in teriyaki sauce for 1 hour.
Grill chicken breasts until done.
Toast onion rolls on grills.
Place chicken/chili strips on onion rolls and top with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: true german potato salad
directions: Saute onion and bacon together.
Slowly add flour so as to avoid lumping.
Add sugar, lowering heat.
Add vinegar and water. Bring to low boil, stirring constantly (mixture looks glassy). Add potatoes (with or without skins), piece by piece, mixing well yet not mashing potatoes.
Season to suit with salt and pepper. Serve hot or lukewarm.
Serves six.

title: curried creamed peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, curry powder, salt and sugar. Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Add milk and lime juice.
Heat to boiling; stir 1 minute.
Add peas; heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: ultimate rocky road
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the milk and chocolate chips; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and sunflower seeds.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add liquid to dry ingredients until flour mixture is moistened. Turn batter into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt and beaten egg yolks together in pan.
Add a little milk to make smooth.
Add cream and enough
milk to make 2 cups.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes
to	a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour in prepared crust and top with meringue.

title: easy cobbler pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Melt margarine in baking dish and pour batter over the melted margarine.
Add fruit and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Batter will rise to top.
This is delicious (try it).

title: baked stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in moderate oven (350°) until soft when pressed, about 45 minutes.
Cut off the top of one long side and carefully remove and mash the pulp.
Reserve the potato cases.
Add other ingredients to the pulp.
Beat well and refill the cases.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: beer-steamed shrimp
directions: Boil water and beer.
Place shrimp in a steamer basket and sprinkle Old Bay and salt to your taste.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
