Add cornstarch and diet soda.
Cook over medium heat until mixtures comes to a boil.
Add apples, spices and lemon juice.
Bring to a second boil.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for about 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or cheese.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: With mixer, cream together butter, sugar and vanilla and almond extracts.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in by hand the flour, salt and soda.
Chill overnight (12 hours).

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: (I use 2 1/2 cups chicken broth instead of granules and water.)

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter.
Mix flour and sugar; add eggs one at a time stirring as little as possible.
Add chocolate mixture, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in muffin pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and crumble.
Brown onion and green pepper.
Add flour, then stir in tomatoes.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add green beans.
Put in heated casserole.
Heat 5 to 10 minutes at 375°. Put crumbled bacon on top before serving.

title: mediterranean fish fillet casserole
directions: Place uncooked Gorton's Fillets in the bottom of an ungreased baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and spoon evenly over fillets.
Cover & cook in the oven at 375 for 25 minutes. Top with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ready-made crust, then cook until done.

title: mustard-topped sirloin steak
directions: Preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
In cup, mix Dijon mustard, prepared white horseradish and the crushed garlic clove. Place steak on rack in broiling pan.
Place pan in broiler at closest position to source of heat; broil steak 10 to 12 minutes for medium-rare or until of desired doneness; with tongs, turn steak once.
Spread mustard mixture evenly over steak and broil 1 to 2 minutes until golden. Cut steak into thin slices to serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: *Carnation dry milk is preferred.

title: easy baked fish
directions: Rinse fish in cold water.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese. Roll fish in mixture.

title: caesar salad
directions: Steep garlic in oil overnight; remove and discard.
Remove crusts from bread; cut bread into small cubes.
Saute bread cubes in 1/4 cup of the garlic oil in a large skillet until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pumpkin pie with bisquick
directions: Beat all ingredients one minute on high speed.
Pour into a well-greased pie tin and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tomato cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine meat, onion, crumbs, pepper, sauce, catsup, garlic, seasoned salt and egg. Mix until well blended.
Spread mixture over bottom of pie shell. Cut tomato in 1/2-inch
slices and arrange around edge of pie.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°. Sprinkle cheese over all and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: open faced tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, apple, onion, walnuts, salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread; top with cheese slices. Broil until cheese is melted.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until brown.

title: blintzes (crepes) with raspberry sauce(makes 10 servings; breakfast - brunch)
directions: In medium bowl, blend flour, milk, egg and margarine.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken into 12 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan.
Put cooked broccoli on top of chicken.
Mix 1 can of milk with both cans of soup and pour over broccoli.
Put prepared Stove Top stuffing on top.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350° or longer if not heated through.

title: aunt jennie's minestrone
directions: In a large pot, crumble ground beef and add all the ingredients except the cheese.
Cook for 1 hour over low heat, stirring now and again.
During the last 5 minutes or so of cooking, add the cup of shredded cheese, mixing it into the minestrone.
When serving, you can add some shredded cheese on top of the minestrone.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut crab meat up or shred.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Serve on lettuce or as a sandwich filling.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing, sugar and vinegar in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly. Refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled.

title: quick and easy strawberry walnut cake
directions: Spread pie filling over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over the top as evenly as possible.
Combine beaten eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add walnuts and pour this mixture over the cake mix.
Stir until well blended.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping or sweetened whipped cream.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Grease 10 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bottom with marshmallows, then prepared cake mix.
Sprinkle on jello granules.
Next spoon on berries, then drizzle water or juice over entire cake.
Don't stir. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 55 minutes.
Serve with more berries and Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
"A real sweet treat!!"

title: nuts and bolts(kid recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix Kix, Cheerios, pretzels and nuts into a large baking pan.
Melt butter in microwave or small pan.
Stir in Worcestershire and salts.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Stir and salt lightly.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring carefully with wooden spoon.
Makes 3 cups.

title: onion bread
directions: Boil milk.
Set off heat and add chopped onion, salt and butter.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of real warm milk.
When cool enough to put finger in, put yeast in mixture.
Add flour.
Put in a warm place to rise until it doubles in size.
Work down real well with greasy hands.
Put in loaf pans and let rise again until it doubles in size.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: quick broccoli pasta
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli and garlic; saute 3 to 4 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in water, bouillon cubes and red pepper.
Cook 2 minutes or until bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Add pasta and toss to coat.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mix. Bake at 350° until done.

title: raspberry topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
In medium bowl beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, ReaLemon juice and if desired, food coloring.
Pour into crust; bake 30 minutes.
Spoon raspberry mixture evenly over top.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: fresh vegetable dip(sweet and sour)
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth.
Serve with fresh vegetables: celery, carrots, cucumbers, broccoli, and/or cauliflower.

title: paw-paw's toad frog toast
directions: Spread toast with oleo or butter.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Put in microwave oven for 3 to 5 minutes, until sugar and cinnamon turn dark.
Slice with an "X" from corner to corner and produce four equilateral triangles per slice.
Serve with a smile.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 package instant pudding, eggs, club soda, oil and nuts as you would to make cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix milk, Dream Whip and 1 pudding mix and frost.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well at medium speed until well blended.
Serve on fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bourbon and brown sugar flank steak
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Marinate for several hours in refrigerator.
Prepare grill.
Place steak on grill rack coated with cooking spray; grill for 5 minutes each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine reserved marinade and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Serve with thickened marinade.

title: three pepper chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine crackers and Italian seasoning. Dip each chicken breast in egg product and coat with cracker mixture. Set aside.

title: cinnamon rolls and sweet bread
directions: To starter, add sugar, oil, salt, warm water and flour.
Set aside and let rise for 8 hours.
Roll out dough into rectangle, 15 x 9-inch.
Spread with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon, brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Roll dough (begin west side). Pinch ends of dough and turn under.
Stretch roll to make even. Cut roll into 15 slices.
Place slightly apart on baking pan or 3 round cake pans or muffin pans (greased).
Let rise for 4 to 5 hours.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: toffee chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate pieces until melted, stirring often.
Stir in sour cream until smooth.
Cut cake in half, horizontally.
Spread with 1/3 of frosting; sprinkle with 1/3 of crushed candy.
Top with second layer.
Frost cake; sprinkle candy on top.
Serves 8 (380 calories per serving).

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.

title: sarah's favorite lasagne
directions: The leg of lamb can be stuffed, rolled and tied the evening before the dinner, covered slightly with waxed paper and refrigerated.
This version also includes oven roasted potatoes, baked with the lamb and basted with the accumulated drippings. Serves 10.

title: peach crisp
directions: Pour peaches in loaf pan; add cake mix on top of peaches. Pour butter over cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Put in buttered casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut pecan caramel pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk. Mix pecans, butter and coconut in saucepan and cook on medium heat until golden brown. Cool this mixture. Fold in Cool Whip into cream cheese mix. Layer cheese mix, coconut pecan mix; drizzle caramel over this. Then repeat. Freeze pies. Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Sift together the flour, salt, cocoa and soda. Add milk and beat, adding vanilla, almond and boiling water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in 5 layers and bake in moderate oven.

title: hot rolls
directions: Beat eggs and add to water, sugar and yeast.
Sift in 3 cups flour and mix well.
Add shortening and salt.
Add 4 cups flour. Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and make out into rolls and let rise again until double.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a spray bottle. Spray over chicken as it is cooking.

title: meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Press firmly into ungreased 8x4x2 meatloaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees about one hour.
Let stand five minutes before slicing.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well. Pour in well-greased skillet or muffin tins (makes 24). Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place biscuits on ungreased pan.
Press each biscuit into small individual crusts.
Spread on sauce.
Apply onions, mushrooms, peppers and cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour into the sugar and egg mixture. Stir well.
Stir in 1 cup of M&M's.
Reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's as desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Combine butter and sour cream; mix until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour.
Stir until blended.
Spoon batter into a 1 3/4-inch muffin pan, filling each with 1 tablespoon of batter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add raisins, if desired.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Heat rhubarb in water. Add sugar.
Mix gelatin in hot rhubarb. Add pineapple and nuts. Congeal.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars
and
stick
butter in saucepan. Set aside; cream
sugar,
eggs
and remaining butter together. Add flour, baking
soda and buttermilk alternately to mixture. Add melted Milky Way bars
and pecans.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at
350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, frost with your favorite light chocolate icing.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat well the shortening, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs with electric mixer.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in coconut, Rice Krispies, oatmeal, vanilla and pecans.
Spoon walnut size drops of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow pan meaty side up.
Cover with thin slices of lemon and onion.
Roast at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Spread each tortilla with a layer of cream cheese. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, salsa, onions and olives. Top with avocado slices. Roll up as tightly as possible and place seam side down on a flat dish. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.

title: elegant steak and rice
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut into strips.
Put vegetable oil in frying pan and cook strips of steak over medium heat until done. Mix garlic salt, cream of mushroom soup and juice from mushrooms in large bowl (makes gravy-like sauce).
When steak strips are done, pour sauce on them.
Cut onion in 1/4-inch rings and lay on top of sauce.
Pour mushrooms on top.
Cover and let simmer until ready to eat.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cocoa into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Add oil in first well, vinegar in second well and the vanilla in the third well.
Pour water over ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put angel food cake mix in bowl.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all to mix.
Cook on bottom rack at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Let cool and cover with cool whip.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate, 9x1 1/4 inches.

title: chilled cantaloupe soup with cinnamon plum starburst
directions: In small saucepan combine wine and cinnamon stick, bring to a boil and reduce to 1/4 cup, stir in honey and chill.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix as other pound cakes.
Put into cold oven. Turn oven to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Add onion.
Pour vegetables into bowl.
Add sugar.
Mix vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: bakery doughnuts
directions: Mix and let set 1 hour, then roll and cut.
Let rise a little. Usually by the time you get them cut, the first ones are ready to fry.
Fry at about 375° and then glaze them.

title: juanita backus' brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Mix sugar with eggs and beat until lemon-colored.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, which have bene sifted together 3 times.
Mix in chocolate.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased wax paper lined pan, size 10 x 7-inch.
When baked, cut at once into 2-inch squares.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Place hash browns in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with salt.
Layer sausage, cheese and green pepper.
Combine eggs and milk, stirring well.
Pour over top of green pepper layer.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spinach veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill, then place in a cut out whole pumpernickel loaf.

title: vanilla nut cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder and salt, then sift again. Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Shape into rolls, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in wax paper; chill overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in a skillet.
Pour soup over vegetables.
Remove fat from skillet and add water to rinse and scrape particles from bottom of skillet.
Pour this over vegetables.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion dip
directions: Combine onion soup mix and sour cream.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Good with potato chips.

title: hot spice cider mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.
For each serving, place 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon of mix in cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well.
Serve hot.
Yields 42 servings.

title: opal's one egg cake
directions: Separate egg.
Set white aside.
Mix flour, sugar, shortening and egg yolk.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat until smooth. Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Beat egg white and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add another teaspoon flavoring.
Spread on top of cake.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: shrimp fry
directions: Dip fresh shrimp into mix and fry.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar to make crust.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: simple strawberry mold
directions: Add water to jello.
In a very large bowl, combine ingredients, alternating the cold items with the jello until smooth.
Transfer into a mold or any serving dish.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Decorate with fresh strawberries and a little whipped cream, if desired.

title: spinach salad with strawberries and pecans
directions: Carefully wash spinach and remove all stems.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Spin dry or pat dry with paper towels.
It is important to remove all extra moisture which will dilute the dressing.
Clean and slice strawberries and place on top of torn spinach leaves and scatter the pecan halves on top.
Add salad dressing (room temperature) just before serving.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and chopped nuts.
(I use walnuts or pecans.)
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans greased and floured.
Cover with cream cheese frosting.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed tomato with cottage cheese
directions: Peel tomatoes and remove a 1/2-inch slice from the top. Remove seeds and pulp from inside tomato.
Sprinkle with salt. Turn upside down and allow to chill about an hour before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat 'n tater pie
directions: Line 9 inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine meat, milk, soup mix, pepper, and allspice; mix gently.
Lightly pat into pastry lined pie plate; top with potatoes.
Place top crust over potatoes; seal and flute edge.
Cut design in top pastry.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Serve with warm catsup if desired.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: the best ceasar salad ever
directions: Srinkle mixture over salad and toss.
Add bacon and croutons and toss. Absolutely Awesome!

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in 1/2 cup of water for 5 minutes.
Mix with carrots, sour cream, soup, mushrooms and 1/2 cup stuffing mix.
Put in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup stuffing with the melted butter.
Place on top of squash mixture. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
If for a lot of people, make a double batch.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry and plain gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, crushed pineapple and juice; add bananas.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into mold.
Set in refrigerator and let jell, then add sour cream.
Spread evenly over.
Pour remainder of jello mixture on top and set in refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Place apples in uncooked pie shell.
Pat flour mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: quick chocolate cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Paper line muffin cups (2 1/2 inches in diameter).
In medium bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat with wire whisk just until blended, batter is smooth and ingredients are well mixed.
Pour batter into paper bake cups; fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; frost as desired.
Yields 18 cupcakes.

title: potato omelette
directions: Saute in peanut oil the potatoes, onions, minced garlic, parsley flakes, salt and pepper to taste; set aside.
Hand beat eggs and water.
Heat nonstick frypan with a pat of butter until butter melts and bubbles.
Pour eggs in and let simmer, adding potato mixture over half of pan.
When egg is cooked, fold omelette.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off grease and add soup, beans and Ro-Tel.
Simmer until all ingredients are heated.
Place Doritos in bottom of casserole.
Pour ground beef mixture over this.
(Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, optional.)
Sprinkle more Doritos on top.
Place in 500° oven for about 5 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Stir in seasoning.
In Tupperware or container that can be covered, place torn lettuce, chopped tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Add kidney beans, then layer meat on top of this.
Blend together mayonnaise and sour cream; pour over all.
Top with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate until serving time. Top with Doritos when served.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sprinkle bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with granola cereal.
In large mixing bowl, using electric mixer on low speed, beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Beat in Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until blended well. Add pumpkin, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into spring-form pan over cereal.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until center is just starting to set.
Turn oven off, with door slightly ajar, for 30 minutes.
Remove pan to wire rack.
Run a knife around side of cake to loosen.
Cool completely.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Freeze.
Serves 16.

title: forget me cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°, then shut oven off.
Drop cookies on sheet; leave in oven overnight or for 8 hours.
Eat and enjoy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the butter, tomato sauce and salt.
Add veggies. Toss vegetables with cheese in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until hot throughout.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creme brulee
directions: Cream the egg yolks with the sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan over low heat.
Slowly stir in the cream.
Add the cinnamon, vanilla and lemon rind.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into molds; cool.
Refrigerate to set.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Debone and cut up meat after boiling until tender.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add chili powder and some garlic.
Stir in soups, tomatoes and chopped chicken.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Boil 1 minute.
While mix is still hot, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; drop on waxed paper.
Let set until firm.
Yields 96 cookies.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except pie crust; mix well. Pour into prepared pie crust. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 35 to 40 minutes, or as directed with one favorite topping or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using only 1 cup of pecans. Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add taco seasoning, reserving 1 Tablespoon.
Add lettuce, onion, tomatoes and cheese in large bowl.

title: meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Break up nuts into pieces at least as small as chocolate chips.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla until whites are stiff.
Gently stir nuts and chocolate into egg whites with a spoon.
Drop batter on parchment paper on a baking sheet in teardrops.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until kisses are hard, but still white.
Makes approximately 36 kisses.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients as given, stirring after each addition is made.
After coconut has been added, mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven, about 300° for one hour.

title: impossible turkey 'n stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix turkey, celery, onion and seasonings in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer green beans on bottom of casserole dish.
Combine sour cream and soup; put mixture on top of green beans.
Add cheese and crushed Ritz crackers to small amount of melted margarine to soften crackers.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: blueberry yum
directions: Boil the berries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water. Cook 15 minutes over low heat. Combine cornstarch
and 1/4 cup water to thicken. Cool.

title: pumpkin bread #2
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in one bowl.
Combine wet ingredients in separate large bowl.
Add dry ingredients slowly to wet ingredients, mixing well.
Grease 2 loaf pans and line bottom with wax paper.
Divide mix in pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.
(This freezes well and makes good muffins, too!)

title: beef pot roast
directions: Rub meat with mixture of salt, chili powder and paprika. Place in roasting pot.
Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: kahlua pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in Kahlua, corn syrup, evaporated milk and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch lined pie pan (Betty Crocker ready made pie crust).
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake until firm (about 40 minutes). Serve chilled or warm slices in microwave.

title: chicken soup
directions: Saute onion and celery until limp, but not brown.
Add broth, potatoes and carrots; simmer until tender.
If necessary, add a little water.
Add cubed chicken; simmer about five minutes to heat chicken; stir gently to avoid breaking up chicken.
Add milk and simmer approximately five more minutes, but do not boil. Serve immediately or reheat from refrigerator, but do not freeze. Great with cornbread and a garden salad.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in seasoned water.
Cool.
Cut in small pieces.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Assemble layer of chicken, layer of asparagus, layer of sauce.
Repeat, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: 93 octane baked beans
directions: Empty baked beans in crock-pot.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 bottle barbecue sauce.
Add Worcestershire to desired taste.
Add ketchup (a lot), mustard (not too much), seasoned salt (cover beans lightly) and almost a full box of brown sugar.
Cook bacon in microwave and then break up in beans.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.
If need to do fast, cook on stove at high heat for 1 hour to 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: white jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water over a pan of hot water.
Set aside to cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add gelatine mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple.

title: joy's chocolate caramel apples on-a-stick
directions: Beat together the sugar, egg yolks and oil along with the hot water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Then add carrots and walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gently fold into mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven in a well-greased tube pan for about 55 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cinnamon dough decorations(child-approved)
directions: To make cinnamon dough, mix together four parts cinnamon, three parts applesauce and one part glue in a bowl.
Give your child a small amount of the dough.
Have them flatten the dough on a floured surface.
Let them use their favorite cookie cutters to cut shapes out of the dough.
Give him/her a straw to make a hole in the top of each shape so it can be hung.
Add ribbons or yarn for hanging after the shapes have dried for at least 48 hours. Sequins, glitter and paper confetti may also be used with glue for decorating.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt together. Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture, fruit and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef. Mix beef with tomato sauce, tomato paste, kidney beans and chili flavoring. Simmer this on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: borracho beans
directions: Cook beans with salt pork until tender (3 to 4 hours approximately).
Fry bacon, onion and tomato.
Add to cooked beans.
Add hot peppers, cilantro and beer.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil and cool the sugar and water.
Mash with mixer the bananas.
Mix rest of ingredients together and then add in sugar water and bananas.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: traditional white bread
directions: Mix 3 1/2 cups of the flour, sugar, salt, shortening and yeast.
Add warm water.
Blend 1 minute on low speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in enough remaining flour, one cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.

title: gingersnaps that crack
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Add molasses. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add and beat.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Dip and roll in sugar.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; beat.
Add Cool Whip (mixture will be light and fluffy.)

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 450°.
Line pan with aluminum foil. Spray generously with Pam.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 1/2-inch wide slices.
Cut each slice into 1/2-inch wide strips. Mix all ingredients.
Toss potatoes in mixture and place in pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, tossing once or twice, until potatoes are crisp and golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gob cake
directions: Beat together in mixer until fluffy (2 to 3 minutes). Divide into 2 (13 x 9) greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 325° for 12 to 20 minutes. Don't overbake. Cool on racks.

title: marzetti
directions: In large skillet, melt 1/2 pound butter.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute on medium heat, stirring constantly, until onion turns clear and pepper is tender.
Stir in beef and pork.
Add seasonings.
Cook uncovered until meat is browned.
Drain well. Cook noodles al dente.
Drain.
Toss with 1/4 cup butter.
Turn into steam table pan.
Stir in well drained meat mixture.
Add celery, tomato soup and mushrooms.
Toss to mix.
Sprinkle cheese to cover top of mixture.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 80.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix 2 cups pickle lime and 2 gallons water in a ceramic cooker.
Slice about 5 to 6 pounds cucumbers.
Soak in lime overnight or 12 hours.
Wash well.

title: shortcut shortcakes
directions: You also need a star shaped cookie cutter.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in pie plate.
Mix dry ingredients together; add melted butter and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger with brown gravy
directions: Make hamburgers out in small patties.
Fry in skillet with chopped onion.
Cook until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Put in pan; pour brown gravy over hamburgers.
Put in oven.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Follow directions on brown gravy mix.

title: tuna vegetable chowder
directions: In a 2-quart container, combine water, potato, onion, carrot, salt, celery salt, pepper, chives and Worcestershire sauce. Cover; microwave on High for 7 to 15 minutes, or until vegetables are just about tender.
Add corn; cover and return to microwave. Heat for 5 to 8 minutes on High, or until corn is tender.
Stir in tuna and cream.
Cover; microwave for 2 to 4 minutes, until heated through.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Combine gelatin with hot water; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add cold water and strawberries.
Chill one-half the mixture for 3 to 4 hours.
Spread with sour cream. Chill for 1 hour.
Carefully spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: gift card recipe for quick apple-cinnamon-bran muffins
directions: Combine muffin mix, egg and water, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon evenly into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Mix Rice Krispies and powdered sugar.
Pour melted mixture over Rice Krispies mixture; mix.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate when chocolate is set.
Put in a covered container.
Keep cool.

title: crock-pot beef barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Fill with water.
Turn on low setting.
Go to work.
It is done whenever you get home.

title: strawberry-banana brownies
directions: Remove stems and hulls from strawberries.
Mash together strawberries and bananas.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, stir together eggs, brownie mix, water and oil just until moistened. Stir in strawberry-banana mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well with a spoon after each addition.
Add cocoa, then flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Yields about 36 brownies.

title: lemon tea muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks; blend yolks with creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture alternating with lemon juice.
(Do not overmix.) Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold whites and lemon peel into batter until everything is mixed.
Fill small greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 18.

title: radish sandwiches on zucchini basil muffins
directions: In a small bowl whisk together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and pepper.
In a bowl cream together shortening and sugar, beat in egg and buttermilk until mixed well.
Stir in zucchini and basil.
Combine both mixtures until blended and divide among 24 well buttered gem tins.
Bake muffins in middle of preheated 400° oven 15 to 18 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Turn onto rack and let cool.
Halve muffins horizontally, spread cut sides with butter, and sandwich radish slices between muffin halves. Makes 24 sandwiches.

title: almond burgers
directions: Combine ingredients and form into patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet until brown.
While browning, heat 2 cans of tomato soup, diluted with 1 can water in a pan.
When patties are brown, turn into the tomato sauce and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes and salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and pull from bone.
Cook broccoli spears until tender.
In sauce pan add cheese, pet milk, mayonnaise, chicken soup, curry, salt and pepper and cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Layer chicken and broccoli and pour cheese sauce over it.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: play doh
directions: Mix water, flour, salt and oil together; add color.
Add cream of tartar.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on low heat until it forms a ball. Remove from heat.
Knead.
Store in and airtight container.

title: tennessee boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs, add other ingredients (except vanilla).
Cook mixture in a double boiler with water below boiling point and cook until mixture coats a spoon.
Cool; add vanilla and nutmeg, if desired.
Serve cold with whipped cream or as floating islands with baked meringue on top.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix the 3 soups with a soup can and a half of water in casserole.
Add rice to mixture.
Top with chicken breasts.
Cut other stick of butter on top.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all well and place in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake
at
for
about	45
minutes
or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cold asparagus
directions: In saucepan, cook vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves, stick cinnamon and celery seed until sugar is dissolved, about 4 minutes.
Place asparagus in shallow dish and cover with the sauce while hot. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from sauce and place in serving dish.
Easy "Do Ahead" dish for a dinner party.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar, margarine, flour, vanilla and soda until like cornmeal.
Save out 1/2 cup.
To mixture, add egg and buttermilk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Heath bars, nuts and caramel mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey-mustard turkey meatballs
directions: In a bowl combine turkey, egg, cracker crumbs, cheese, onion, ginger and 3 tablespoons mustard.
Form into 30 balls, 1-inch each.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until juices run clear. Combine pineapple juice, green pepper, honey, cornstarch and onion powder.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more; reduce heat.
Stir in remaining mustard until smooth.
Brush meatballs with 1/4 cup sauce and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serve remaining sauce as a dip for meatballs.	Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: deer steak in crock-pot
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender.
Pour off broth.
Add 2 cans mushroom soup.
Add 1 cup milk.
Cook on low for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar with paddle.
Add the warm milk.
Mix all spices together and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 or 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: maple fudge
directions: Mix the 5 ingredients and let boil on low heat 15 minutes. In a bowl, put 1 cup marshmallow cream and 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour hot mixture over marshmallow cream and peanut butter and beat until it starts to thicken. Pour in greased pan.

title: marilyn green's sugar cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the flour mixture.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple yogurt trifle
directions: Evenly divide half of the chopped apple pieces among four parfait dishes or tall glasses.
Divide yogurt from container among dishes.
Add 2 tablespoons Grape-Nuts to each trifle, then top with layers of remaining yogurt, chopped apple and sprinkle of Grape-Nuts on top.
Refrigerate at least 15 to 20 minutes before serving to allow cereal to soften slightly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Blend soup and 3/4 can of milk.
Add vegetables and chicken. Put in casserole dish and in oven until bubbling at 425°.
Place biscuits on top.
Return to oven
until biscuits brown.

title: meat pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Brown beef and drain off fat. Add tomato sauce to mixture; add chili powder and garlic salt. Cook
until
thick;
flatten
biscuits in the bottom of baking dish.
Spoon
meat
sauce over biscuits.
Add shredded cheese over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken in dish.
Pour rice around chicken.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup on top. Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: harvest time goulash
directions: Cook noodles.
Rinse and drain thoroughly.
Prepare mixed vegetables per package directions.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine sugar, wine vinegar and olive oil.
Boil 1 minute and cool.
In 2-quart bowl, combine drained green beans, peas and corn.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours, stirring often.

title: chicken tandoori
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle with onion, garlic, green pepper, tomatoes, salt and spices.
Pour melted butter over all.
Add stock and bake, basting frequently.
Bake 50 minutes and serve with white rice.

title: layer bake
directions: Put butter onto 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Watch closely while melting.
Remove from oven, sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Save condensed milk for last.
Pour milk evenly over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: black-eyed susans
directions: Bring cheese and butter to room temperature.
Beat with electric mixer until combined. Add flour, 2 tablespoons water, salt and pepper.
Stir until combined.
If crumbly, add water.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with hands the confectioners sugar, oleo and peanut butter.
Make small balls.
Refrigerate until you melt chocolate.
Melt in double boiler the paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Dunk balls in chocolate with toothpick.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed on package.
In bowl combine Ricotta, Parmesan and eggs.
Mix well.
On bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish spread 1/2 cup pasta sauce.
Top with half each of lasagna noodles, cheese mixture, sausage, sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering; top with parsley.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover. Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: hazel's green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix green beans, soup, milk and 1/2 cup onions, broken into pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir, then sprinkle the remaining onions over bean mixture.
Bake 5 minutes more or until onions are golden.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Put mayo, pimientos, Worcestershire sauce and mustard into blender.
Process until smooth, then put in cheese cubes.
Process again until blended (creamy).
Serve over small bread.

title: walnut honey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In a large saucepan, heat milk and add honey and sugar, stirring until sugar is melted and homogeneous, then cool.
Mix in butter and egg yolks.
Sift together flour, salt and soda then mix in thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake about an hour or until knife comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and turn out on rack to cool thoroughly. Wrap well and store.
Better second day.

title: angel tarts
directions: Take premixed Jell-O instant cheesecake mix and beat in cream cheese. Fold in your Cool Whip, then refrigerate according to package directions. Fill your prebaked phyllo cups with mixture. Set aside. Warm your fruit pie filling of choice on stove. Take a small spoon and apply small amounts of topping onto your tart. Refrigerate for approximately 30 minutes, then serve.

title: sensational shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl; refrigerate.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Prep time:
10 minutes plus refrigeration.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes for a medium-large casserole.
Cook until tender and drain.
Melt margarine; stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk slowly until it gets thick and smooth.
Pour over potatoes and add Spam.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: heavenly punch
directions: Boil 1	quart
water.
Add
jello.
When
cool, add all ingredients in gallon jug.	Finish filling with cool water and let set 24 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot garlic spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl and serve spread on freshly made toast.
Store in refrigerator.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix together and store covered in refrigerator.

title: easy cheesy mushroom dip
directions: Mix the soup and cream cheese in the microwave or on top of the stove until hot and well blended.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in ice cream maker.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan and let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until it forms a soft ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Pour half of the syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue to beat.
Return syrup to heat. Continue cooking until it forms hard ball.
Sprinkle in jello gradually, then pour remaining syrup over first mixture, beating until candy loses its gloss.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: brown sugar pies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, butter and milk, then add vanilla. Bake in 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Put pecans in bottom of crusts, then pour mixed ingredients over the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Stew raisins till tender. Drain and add cream, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Mix well and cook until mixture thickens.
Add nuts.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with egg whites, beaten stiff. Bake until meringue is brown.
If you want, you can leave off meringue and use whole eggs where it calls for egg yolks. It is just as good.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a large dry bowl.
Stir until well blended. Pack into jars, making sure a piece of vanilla bean is in each jar.
Seal and label.
Store in refrigerator at least a week before using to allow vanilla flavor to be absorbed into the mix. Makes 8 cups mocha mix.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo in medium saucepan.
Add sugar and well beaten eggs. Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Mix all this very well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice and add water to make 1 cup. Blend together the Splenda, cornstarch, egg and salt. Heat over low heat with juice/water mixture until thickened. Cool. Cut up the fruit and mix cooled dressing with fruit. Enjoy!

title: fast and easy fruit sauce
directions: Combine the fruit and juice and sugar in blender (or food processor) and mix until smooth. Pour into 1 qt. pan and cook over medium heat until heated through. Remove from heat and stir in butter-flavored extract. Serve warm over pancakes, french toast or waffles. Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Trim, seal and flute edges; set aside. In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt. In a large mixing bowl, beat buttermilk, eggs, butter, lemon juice, lemon peel and vanilla. Add to sugar mixture; mix well. Pour into crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together; form into balls. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover potatoes with melted butter. Fry pork chops and put on potatoes. Mix soup and milk together. Pour over pork chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle top with shredded Cheddar cheese and rebake until melts.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Cut cooled potatoes into cubes.
Combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing.
Add crumbled bacon.
Toss gently.
Add salt, pepper and paprika as desired.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Drop shredded cabbage into boiling water; boil 10 minutes. Drain.
Put half of the cabbage in a 9 x 14-inch buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with half of the salt, pepper and sugar.
Add flour and cheese and half the butter.
Put in the rest of the cabbage, salt, pepper, sugar and butter.
Top with bread crumbs and pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
(Bread crumbs are coated with remaining half of butter, melted, before they are put on top of casserole.)

title: chocolate lover's frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat 1 cup confectioners sugar, Nestle cocoa, butter, 2 tablespoons milk and vanilla extract until creamy.
Gradually add remaining confectioners sugar alternately with remaining milk.
Beat until smooth.
Frosts one 8 or 9-inch layer cake.
Makes 2 1/3 cups frosting.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of muffin tins.
Combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Add milk, oil and egg and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Dice
medium
size zucchini.
Mix together all ingredients and
put
in casserole in 350° oven for 1 hour, stirring once during the baking time.

title: baked water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with bacon.
Secure with toothpick. Place in ungreased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Spoon sauce over chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo; place crushed grahams in 9 x 9-inch square pan and pour oleo on top.
Pour milk on top and cover grahams.
Top with coconut, then chocolate chips and finally pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, until chocolate chips are melted and milk is slightly browned.
Cool completely and cut into 9 squares.

title: mile high icing
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Cook 1 cup milk and 4 tablespoons of flour until thick.
Let cool, then add a pinch of salt and vanilla and mix with other ingredients.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate, adding flour and milk.
Add vanilla flavoring. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased/floured cake pan.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and butter thoroughly.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add nuts.
Top with walnut halves.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add juice from pineapple and water to equal 1 1/4 cups.
Cook until begins to thicken.
Add margarine; pour over sausage, yams and pineapple arranged in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add ginger ale and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons lemon juice over peaches.
Fold peaches, celery and nuts into thickened gelatin.
Chill until firm in 8
or 9-inch square pan.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with your favorite fruits.
Enjoy!

title: ice cream watermelon
directions: In Tupperware
lettuce
keeper,
put lime sherbet, softened, around edges and sides of Tupperware.
Put into freezer to harden. In
the
meantime,
soften strawberry or raspberry ice cream or sherbet.
Add
chocolate chips to ice cream.
Put into Tupperware to harden in freezer.

title: new york blondies with white chocolate chunks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Baker's Joy. In saucepan over low heat, melt butter and brown sugar together until sugar dissolves. Let cool. Pour in mixing bowl. Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, baking powder, salt, nuts, white chocolate chunks and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake. Cut in squares while hot and cool in pan.

title: kibbee
directions: After trimming all the fat from steak, cut into pieces to fit into grinder.
Grind twice.
Soak burghul 5 mins in enough water to cover after it was washed once or twice.
Grind pepper, onion, mint and basil and add to meat.
Add salt, spices and burghul. Burghul should be squeezed to remove all water before adding to meat.
Mix meat mixture by hand till well blended.
Add ice water as you mix to keep meat soft.
Consistency should not be too dry, more like a moist meat loaf mixture before cooking.
Arrange in flat dish, garnish with parsley or mint sprigs.
Serve with oil and pita bread.
Leftover kibbee may be cooked the next day.

title: brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar; then add melted chocolate and flour mixture.
Then add vanilla and nuts, mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead until mixture no longer sticks to your fingers.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Roll into 1-inch balls and store.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and mix well and add jam.
Add soda to buttermilk and then to mixture.
Add flour and mince meat. Bake in a tube pan at 325 until done.
May bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or in three 8-inch pans.

title: shamrock salad
directions: Combine cheese, olives and nuts.
Cut peppers into rings and arrange on pineapple slices.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Serve with French dressing on lettuce leaves.

title: grandmom burgoyne's scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters well!
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Put in oysters, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Cover with bread slices broken up.
Put pepper on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salsa(mild)
directions: Mix together and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: In a heavy soup kettle, melt butter.
Add oil.
Add onion, scallions and garlic.
Add celery and cauliflower.
Add seasonings.
Mix well.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for several minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water and miso.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Remove cover and cool slightly. Puree in small increments in a blender until smooth and creamy. Reheat, adding fresh ground nutmeg.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
In a large pan, saute bell pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken.
Alternate in large casserole dish, Doritos, chicken and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fast peach cobbler
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and milk; set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Pour batter on top of melted butter. Do not mix.
Add fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Leave as layered. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: my favorite chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk together in shallow, wide bowl.
Set aside. Mix together bread crumbs and cake mix in another shallow wide bowl.
Dip cut up chicken first in egg mixture, then into crumb mix.
Lightly grease cookie sheet and put well coated chicken on to bake.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes; turn as needed.

title: fat-free black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas and remove stones.
Combine peas, onion, cumin seed, oyster sauce and bay leaves in water.
Slow cook until peas are soft with lid on pot; stir occasionally.
Serve peas over boiled or steamed rice.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Melt and bring to boil butter, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Mix with sugar and flour.
Add eggs, baking soda, vanilla, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jello
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press mixture firmly into pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes until brown at 375°.
Cool.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water and cool.
Take cream cheese and sugar and cream together.
Add Cool Whip or dessert whip and mix into cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Pour cooled Jell-O over cheese mixture.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate and add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix together and let stand 24 hours.
Roll onto wax papered cookie sheets to 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 150° until leathery.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together flour, allspice, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Stir together buttermilk and soda.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk mixture into the shortening mixture and mix for 2 minutes.
Add diced apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: ranch style lima beans
directions: Squeeze or mash the tomatoes. Place all of the ingredients (except bacon) into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Lay bacon slices across the top. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: lumpia (from philippines)
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add pork, shrimp, garbanzos and ham.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add carrots, green beans, hearts of palm and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in cabbage and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook, covered, for 7 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Cool.

title: manicotti genovese
directions: Cook onion with garlic and basil in butter until tender.
Add soup, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add chicken.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients
and spread on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt the next 2 ingredients.
Stir until smooth and spread over cooled oatmeal mixture.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: milk punch
directions: Combine punch, milk and ice cream.
Stir until ice cream begins to melt.
Add soda to mixture just before serving.

title: top of stove cookies(date)
directions: Boil until thick.
Cool.
Roll into balls and then roll in coconut to cover.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let set out until room temperature.
Mix grated cheese and Bisquick into sausage.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place balls size of walnuts onto sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
May serve hot or cold.

title: pecan ring(serves 15 to 20)
directions: Mix and pour into two oiled, floured bread pans or the new nonstick bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except hamburger.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into a greased iron skillet.
Spread the hamburger on top, then layer the remaining cornmeal mixture.
You can grate some more cheese and top with this if you like.
Use 3 to 4 jalapenos, if you do not like it too hot.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kathy's persimmon pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Bake until firm and well done in a 350° oven.

title: sausage-apple stuffing
directions: In large saucepot over medium heat, cook sausage until browned, breaking pieces apart with fork.
Remove with slotted spoon to bowl.
Pour all but 1/4 cup drippings from saucepan.
In drippings over medium heat, cook apples, onion and celery until celery is tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in sausage and remaining ingredients and mix. Makes enough stuffing for 1 (7 to 9 pound) bird or 6 1/4 cups.

title: holiday cheeseball
directions: Mix ingredients together
and form into cone shape.
Roll your cone in chopped parsley.
Cut up a red pepper (color optional) into little squares.
Put on cone in garland-fashion.
Alternate garlend rows with peanuts.
Peel a lemon; cut out two star shapes and put on top of tree back-to-back.
Serve on platter surrounded by crackers and vegetables.

title: sausage balls
directions: Warm sausage at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Mix thoroughly all items.
Roll in small balls, size of a quarter.
Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: cheese-frosted cauliflower(easy and quick)
directions: Wash cauliflower; remove leaves and cut out base.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Place cauliflower in shallow ungreased baking pan.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over cauliflower and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with tomato wedges and parsley, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cardamon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in egg.
Add yeast, salt, cardamon, milk and flour and knead.
Let it raise for 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down and braid.
Rise it for 40 more minutes.
Brush with milk and sugar. Grease baking sheet.
Oil hands when working with dough.
Cook in oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt stick of oleo.
Add crushed Ritz crackers to make crust. Press into bottom and sides of 9
x 13-inch cake pan.
Soften 1/2 gallon ice cream and add 2 small packages instant pudding.
Place this mixture in crust.
Top with Cool Whip and reserve 2/3 cup crushed crackers and freeze.
Thaw a little before serving.

title: williamsburg apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk to make batter.
(If batter is too stiff, add a little more milk.)
Pour over melted butter.
Mix apple pie filling with lemon, cinnamon, nutmeg and raisins to taste.
Smooth gently over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Stir in eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, then stir into shortening mixture.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Drain water.
Pick chicken off the bone.
Boil spaghetti noodles until tender.
Add noodles, onions or peppers and Ro-Tel to the chicken.
Cook in big pot on top of the stove.
Add Velveeta cheese on top.
Makes a big pot.

title: fresh basil and tomato salad
directions: Prepare at least 1 hour before serving.
Arrange tomatoes on a serving platter or flat storage container.
Top with basil leaves and onion slices to taste.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle with vinegar and pepper.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Fry chicken wings in as small amount of oil as possible until browned and tender.
Remove; drain on paper towels.

title: chunky chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy. Mix flour with soda and salt. Blend into butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chunks, coconut and nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop 2 inches apart by heaping tablespoons on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool 2 minutes before removing from sheets.
Yield: 2 dozen 3 inch cookies.

title: pumpkin cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1 tablespoon milk and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and beat together.
Spread in pie crust.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Chop vegetables and cover them with boiling water and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain water off.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Pour Pepsi and ketchup in a bowl; mix together.
Put chicken in a large frying pan.
Pour Pepsi and ketchup mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 more minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until moist.
Drop from spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften and cream the cream cheese.
Add green pepper, onion and salt and cream together.
Squeeze juice from pineapple, then blot with paper towel.
Add pineapple and pecans to rest of mixture.
Form in a ball and chill about 1 hour.
Then roll in chopped pecans.

title: seafood casserole(serves 6)
directions: Crush crackers; set aside 1 cup.
Beat eggs; add to milk. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom and sides of 3-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Alternate layers of crackers and seafood.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Top with 1 cup of crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon honey butter
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat until soft and fluffy.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 1 cup.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make
a
one-crust pie.
Combine the ingredients in the order given
and	pour
into
pie
pan.	Bake
at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: 60 dollar creole gumbo
directions: *If loose hot sausage is used, such as Pete's brand, remove some of the sausage from the skin and allow it to cook apart in the broth.

title: monkey bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter each biscuit and roll pieces in sugar mixture; place in Bundt pan. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over biscuit pieces.
Melt butter and add brown sugar; drizzle over biscuit pieces.
Bake for 35 minutes and invert pan over large plate after baking.

title: golden fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line 10-inch tube pan with foil.
Cut cherries in half.
Reserve 15 for garnish.

title: flourless chocolate cake for passover
directions: Grease an 8 x 2-inch round pan or 8-inch spring-form pan with 1 tablespoon butter; dust pan with cake meal.
Refrigerate.
Mix chocolate with remaining 6 tablespoons of butter in top of double boiler; simmer until melted.
In another bowl, mix 7 egg yolks. Add 1/4 cup of chocolate; stir well.
Add rest of chocolate; stir well.
Heat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites with salt to soft peaks. Add sugar 1 teaspoon at a time until stiff and glossy.
Pour and scrape chocolate mixture over meringue.
Fold well.
Pour into pan; bake until center is set, but still jiggles slightly, about 60 minutes.
Invert while still hot or remove sides if spring-form pan.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cran-apple chops
directions: Coat a skillet with cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat. Sprinkle pork chops with black pepper and salt. Put chops in the skillet and brown on each side.
Add apple juice or cider.
Cover tightly; cook on low 5 or 6 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine cranberry sauce, brown sugar or honey, orange juice, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour over the chops.
Cook for 2 or 3 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cookie crumb crust(no bake)
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine crushed cookies and margarine. Generously spray pie plate or pan. With the back of a spoon or with fingers, press cookie mixture into pie plate. Cover bottom and sides. Chill until ready to use. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: bradley's corn dogs
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, salt and dry mustard.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Mix egg and milk together; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: fish in shrimp sauce(fisk i rekesaus)
directions: Roll and fasten fish with toothpick or if fillet is thick, cut into serving pieces.
Poach in boiling water until flaky or until it rises to surface.
Remove and drain, reserving 1 cup stock for sauce.
Make a white sauce with butter, flour, fish stock, cream and lemon.
Arrange fish in 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with white sauce and shrimp.
Sprinkle with cheese and dill weed (optional). Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: yule pudding
directions: Cream shortening, spices, peels, molasses, salt and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add carrots, apples and lemon juice. Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with milk.
Add currants and nuts.
Mix well.
Fill well-greased pudding mold 2/3 full.
Cover and steam for 2 hours.
Serve warm with Fluffy Hard Sauce.

title: honey butter
directions: Combine all with a whisk or spatula.

title: "pop off" or "coffee can bread"
directions: Dissolve yeast, ginger, 1 tablespoon sugar and water in a warm bowl until it bubbles about 10 minutes.
Then add 2 tablespoons sugar, evaporated milk, salt and oil.
Add flour one cup at a time until dough is heavy and thick.
Sprinkle on enough flour to handle then divide into two halves.
Put in two well greased coffee cans (1 pound) and cover with well-greased plastic lids. Let stand in warm place to rise.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a double boiler. Use mixer to stir.
Beat briskly 3 minutes or until frosting is fluffy and holds shape.
Add vanilla.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a small mixing bowl or onto sheet of wax paper, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: When mashing potatoes, use just enough milk and butter to make a stiff mixture.
Fry hamburger and onion; pour off fat.
Add thyme, salt, pepper and carrots.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Thicken with flour and pour over hamburger.
Put 1/2 of potatoes in casserole.
Pour meat mixture over potatoes and cover with rest of potatoes.
Smooth potatoes with a fork.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onion in heavy skillet until meat is browned. Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 6 ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and eggs.
Stir well to blend. Spoon a small amount of meat sauce into a lightly greased baking dish.

Layer with half of each of lasagna noodles, cheese mixture, pepperoni, meat sauce and mozzarella cheese. Repeat layer with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake in 350 degree oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° to 500° until golden brown.

title: fruit and cream cheese
directions: Place fruit on dish; save 2 tablespoons fruit juice or fruit syrup.
Pour onto softened cream cheese.
Mix well and add pecans. Place a spoonful of cheese into the center of each fruit and chill.

title: overnight lettuce salad(best made the day before serving.)
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in pan.
Spread with mayonnaise, then sprinkle with sugar.
Distribute cheese and bacon over all. Refrigerate, cover with foil.
Best made day before.

title: cajun chili
directions: Saute onion and pepper in a small amount of oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 hours. Can be frozen.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers.
Add tomatoes and sauce. Cook macaroni as directed.
When done, mix in large bowl.

title: vegetarian enchiladas
directions: Finely chop onions and bell peppers; saute.
Add stewed tomatoes, chopped chilies and chopped garlic.
Add cumin to taste. Cook down until thick.
Roll mixture into flour tortillas.
Add olives and 1 to 2 spoons sour cream and Cheddar cheese to each tortilla.
Place tortillas in a pan; pour any remaining sauce over them.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fruity cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake, using pineapple juice instead of water. Mix all of the above ingredients together and beat until fluffy. Ice the cake with the Cool Whip mixture.
Garnish with pineapple and coconut, or anything you like.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles 15 minutes; drain.
Brown ground beef, pour off fat.
Line bottom of baking dish with noodles, sour cream, American cheese, ground beef, Ragu sauce and grated cheese. Repeat layers and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: Clean as much out with paper towels as possible.
Using full strength ammonia, dab on jam.
Jam should start coming off immediately.
Clean as much off as possible.
Soak area with sponge and leave sponge in place for 1 hour.
Clean with paper towels.
Place newspaper and weight over wet spot overnight.
Wash in washer.
Inspect stain before putting in dryer.
If stain is still present, repeat procedure.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Steam vegetables in
broth
or
fat
until
tender; add tomato paste,
red pepper, chili pepper, Worcestershire sauce, olives, mushrooms and
pimento
to
chicken.
Cook
noodles in broth until tender.
Mix carefully with other mixture.
If too dry, add water, broth or tomato sauce.
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk in bowl until creamy.
Stir in cheese, macaroni and beef.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Chill for 3 to 4 hours to overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a heavy pot, heat the oil.
Add onions, garlic and dry mustard.
Cook until soft, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, including lemon rinds.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard rinds.
Pour in a jar and store in refrigerator.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain juice from one can of clams. Melt butter and add drained clams, then add other can of clams, crumbs, onion and lemon juice.
Pour into shallow baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with lightly salted crackers.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 2-quart round casserole. In large bowl, with fork, mix flour, sugar, salt and baking soda. Using 2 knives in scissor fashion, cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
In small bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Remove 1 tablespoon and reserve. Add buttermilk to remaining eggs and stir into flour mixture until mixture is moistened.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Turn dough onto well-floured surface.
With well-floured hands, knead dough about 10 times.
Shape into ball; place in casserole.
In center of dough, cut a 4-inch cross 1/4-inch deep.
Brush dough with reserved egg.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in dish on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from dish and cool completely on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hopscotch no bake cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add peanut butter and marshmallows. Add chow mein noodles.
Drop by spoon on platter or cookie sheet. Let cool until set.

title: verdenna's goulash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed on box. Brown hamburger with green pepper and onions.
Drain.
Mix macaroni, hamburger, spaghetti sauce, green pepper and onion in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle on top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: light stuffed french toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Arrange half of the bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.

title: cream broccoli soup
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until all is tender.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter; stir thoroughly.
Add eggs. Roll as for pastry.
Cut into 1/2 x 3-inch strips; bake at 375° until brown.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Sprinkle ground cinnamon on work surface and knead dough until it is smooth.
Sprinkle work surface with more cinnamon, as needed, and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters. Poke a hole in shape for hanging.

title: easy elegant cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Pour crumbs into spring-form pan.
Mold with hands to bottom of pan.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Combine beans; divide into four equal batches (about 3 3/4 each).
To make one batch of soup:
Wash one batch of beans.
Place in a large kettle; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Drain and rinse beans. Return to kettle; add spices and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove spices.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Yield:
One batch makes 14 servings (3 1/2 quarts).

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Crust:
In a bowl, put 2 cups flour, shortening and salt. Work with a fork until it looks like sand.
Add ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time until moist.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and line pie pan.
Use 1/2 for the top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
together
flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, carrots and pecans.
Then combine sugar, oil, pineapple, eggs and vanilla; add to first mixture.	Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.
