title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Fill cupcake papers 3/4 full. Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large 5-gallon stockpot, brown meat in shortening. Add onion and seasonings. Add stock to meat and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until meat is just tender. Do not overcook (do not want beef mushy). In large bowl, mix flour, water and Worcestershire sauce and stir until smooth. Add to the meat while stirring and cook until thickened. Add sour cream to meat mixture, stirring constantly. Add mushrooms. Heat to 180°. Place into two 12 x 20 x 6 pans plus one 12 x 9 x 6. Keep warm in oven until you serve. Makes 250 (6 ounce) portions.

title: pecan butter pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Place broken pecans on pastry. Beat eggs.
Add above ingredients and pour over pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all together, then pour in a baked shell.
Top with a layer of
Cool Whip topping.
Chill for an hour.

title: cindy's roast delight
directions: Coat shallow roasting pan with olive oil.
Place meat in center.
Quarter potatoes (skins on) and place around meat. Coat potatoes with remainder of olive oil. Sprinkle Lipton soup over meat and potatoes. Add water around potatoes.
Place in a 325° oven and let simmer, turning meat and potatoes every 15 minutes until done (approximately 2 hours). Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; a little water will help bind mix.
Roll into small balls (1-inch diameter).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rosemary's caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; blend in sugar and salt.
Stir in syrup and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until candy reaches 244° (boiling stage).
Boil for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and cut.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Measure 1 cup of mixture; set aside.
Pat remaining mix in an ungreased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat the cream cheese, egg, lemon juice and sugar until smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle the remaining cup of mix over all.
Bake 12 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: london broil or flank steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate steak at least 4 hours.
Better overnight, even longer.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes or until brownies pull from pan.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Place all ingredients, except tortillas and picante sauce, in a food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and wrap in damp paper towels.
Place in a Ziploc bag and chill.

title: buttery herb-cheese muffins
directions: Stir together all ingredients just until blended.
Spoon muffin batter into lightly greased miniature muffin pans, filling to the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Add molasses and beat well.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Beat until smooth. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Combine all ingredients except rolls.
Roll out dough and cut into squares.
Spread 1/2 of squares with chicken filling.
Top with remaining dough.
Pinch dough with fork.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with chicken sauce gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamsicle shakes
directions: Place 5 scoops of ice cream into blender. Pour orange soda into blender until it comes about halfway to top of ice cream. Blend until smooth and thick.
Place a spoon of ice cream in cup. Pour creamsicle mix over ice cream.

title: copper pennies(carrot salad)
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water until tender (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Drain, combine carrots, onion and peppers in large bowl.
Pour other ingredients over vegetables. Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Remove skin and bones from the salmon, but do not drain.
Mix salmon and liquid together with the remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: strawberry tart
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar like flaky dough.
Form in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sour cream and corn; add peppers and onion. Stir in meal gradually adding milk for desired thickness, then add cheese, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with chili or by itself.

title: turtle fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix by box directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt butter, caramels and evaporated milk together; pour over cake, then sprinkle on chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (no longer).
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, oatmeal and milk in bowl. Shape into balls.
Brown in hot skillet and place in baking dish. Blend brown sugar, dry mustard, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and catsup, mixing well.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil sugar, water and cranberries until berries pop.
Add jello and stir until jello has dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a large glass dish and refrigerate overnight.
Serves about 20.

title: texas taco dip
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer ingredients in a flat dish in this order: bean dip, avocado mixture, taco mixture, chopped green onions, chopped tomatoes, chopped ripe olives and cheese.

title: herb sticks
directions: Let buns stand a day to partially dry.
Combine oleo, chives, parsley, dill, oregano and garlic powder.
Melt butter or oleo; add seasonings.
Use pastry brush and apply to bars.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl and mix (with hand) until you can roll into little balls.
If mixture is too dry, add a small amount of milk to better shape balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet and place in freezer until they harden.
Store in plastic bags until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and crisp. Yields about 50 to 75.

title: stir-fry sesame green beans
directions: In a large nonstick skillet or wok, stir-fry beans over medium-high heat in oil for 2 minutes. Add sweet pepper and mushrooms; stir-fry 2 minutes longer. Add green onions and garlic; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Makes a double crust.
Save extra for other use.
Blend shortening and flour to make crumbs.
Add salt and water to make soft pastry.
Refrigerate and roll.

title: peppernuts
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until well beaten, adding sugar as you beat eggs.
Add 2 cups flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, citron and
nutmeg.
Stir until well mixed.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix everything but nuts, cake mix and oleo.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Sprinkle nuts over mix.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo and pour over top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 250° until done.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook
chicken (boil or bake) and chop into pieces.
Mix chicken meat, soup, sour cream and chopped olives into a large bowl.
Add	onions.
Heat vegetable oil in a small frying pan; dip each
tortilla
in the hot oil to soften.	Drain on paper towels. Fill
each
cooked tortilla with mixture and sprinkle with
some grated cheese and roll.
Put in pan with seam down. Pour
the remaining mixture over the top and then top the pan with
chopped onions
and
cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Adapt to	your own taste.
I like to put everything in the tortilla except some grated cheese for the top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dredge dates and nuts in flour mixture.
Beat eggs well; add cooking oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Mix dry and liquid ingredients together.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: quickie beef and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Heat in oven until all is hot and cheese is melted.
Can also add mixed vegetables, if desired.

title: new england boiled dinner(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Peel potatoes and onions.
Peel carrots and cut into 3 to 4-inch pieces.
Place potatoes, onions and carrots into large 6 to 8-quart pot with water to cover.
Cover and bring vegetables to a boil, then reduce heat and cook about 30 minutes.
Drain string beans.
Add meat and string beans with water, if necessary, to cover.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix and add enough milk to spread.
Return to oven and brown.

title: crock-pot applesauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
Serve with chunks or use mixer to make it smoother. Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese together until well blended.
Add sugar to mixture and cream until light and
fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla. Add flour and salt.
Spoon batter into a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out on a wire rack and cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cream of crab
directions: Heat milk and cream over low to medium heat to scalding (do not boil).
Stir.
When hot, add bouillon and butter.
Stir with soup on low.
Takes time to melt butter.
When butter is almost melted, pour in cornstarch slowly while stirring.
Add salt and pepper to taste (use white pepper).
Put in crab meat.
Add sherry to this. Start with 1/4 cup in single recipe.
Add while hot.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl, by hand for 1 minute.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour.
Cool slightly before slicing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice
and
cook
squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, salt, pepper, 1/2 Cheddar cheese, milk and egg. Put in a buttered casserole dish.	Sprinkle with 1/2 cup
cheese and Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours and serve with crackers.

title: pedro's special
directions: Brown ground round and chopped onion together.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple (juice and all) with dry pudding.
Add rest of ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: green beans and corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine corn, green beans, celery, onions, sour cream and celery soup. Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with crackers. Drizzle margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until hot and bubbly. Serves 8.

title: pork chop and sauerkraut dish
directions: In a large Dutch oven or roasting pan, put kraut, potatoes, sausages and pork chops.
Slice butter over all.
Put in a 300° oven and let roast with cover on all day.

title: easy beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients in bottom of foil lined pan.
Close foil tightly and bake for 2 or 3 hours or until brisket is tender.
Let set for 10 minutes, then slice and eat.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook the noodles until tender (about 15 minutes) in 1 1/2 quarts boiling water to which 1 1/2 teaspoons salt has been added. Lightly brown the onion in butter.
Add the ground chuck and cook slowly until brown.
This will take about 10 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add cooked noodles.
Add Veg-All including the liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
If you want a top on your dish you may use 1 small can of biscuits and spread them over the top, then bake.

title: greek wedding cookies(kourambiethes 11)
directions: Beat butter with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Dissolve baking soda in lemon juice; add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla, cognac and almonds.
Gradually add the flour; knead until soft about 15 minutes.
Pinch off small amount of dough and shape as desired about 1/2 inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with rosewater.
While still warm, dip each cookie into a bowl filled with sifted powdered sugar.
Press the sugar all around with fingers.
Place on brown paper and sprinkle tops generously with additional sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 30 large or 50 small cookies.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix dates and nuts.
Cover them as thoroughly as possible with flour to which salt and baking powder have been added.
Beat sugar and egg yolks, add flavoring.
Add to date mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter (heavy).
Pour into tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken ribbons satay
directions: Combine peanut butter, water, soy sauce, garlic, lemon juice, brown sugar, ginger and red pepper flakes in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute or until smooth.
Cool.
Remove garlic from sauce; discard.
Reserve half of sauce for dipping. Cut chicken lengthwise into 1-inch strips.
Thread onto 8 metal or bamboo skewers.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix to blend. Chill.

title: apricot candy roll
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in a heavy skillet to soft ball stage (236°).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat by hand until stiff enough to knead.
Put on board; knead until smooth.
Shape into roll.
Chill; cut in slices.

title: cheddar potatoes with broccoli
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and shape into dish.
Cook and drain 2 packages whole spear broccoli.
Layer on top of ingredients in dish.
Add layer of a can of French fried onions and sprinkle some more shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter with sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1/2 the flour mix.
Beat until smooth.
Add remainder of flour mixture with hands.
Add nuts.
Chill, wrapped in foil.
Grease pan.
Slice and bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend zucchini, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: scallops florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in heavy 12-inch skillet over medium to low heat.
Add garlic and saute approximately 3 minutes.
Add spinach and saute another 5 minutes.
Add whipping cream, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in scallops, pasta and half the cheese. Pour into shallow 4-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake until scallops are just opaque, about 10 to 12 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken-pork satay
directions: Place chicken and pork in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Combine cream of coconut, lime, vegetable oil, teriyaki, coriander, ground pepper and garlic.
Pour over meat.
Seal bag and marinate meat in refrigerator 4 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Soak 24 (6-inch) bamboo skewers in water 30 minutes; set aside.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Cut up flour, salt and shortening.
Mix remaining ingredients. Add to cut up mixture.

title: el paso cottage cheese
directions: Mix cottage cheese, avocado, green onions, green chilies and garlic salt.
Garnish with tomato wedges, chopped green onions and bacon bits before serving.

title: macaroni tuna dish
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook green pepper, celery and onion together.
Combine tuna, macaroni and vegetables.
Make white sauce and add to tuna dish.
Heat through.
Serve with potato chips.
Quick and tasty.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan and mix with crushed cookies. Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan like crust.
Mix the pudding with the milk and beat until thick.
Add the ice cream to this mixture and pour over crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Put Cool Whip on top. Crush the Heath Bars and sprinkle over the Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice and pudding.
Cook until it is thick.
Set aside and let cool. Add all the other fruit together while pudding is cooling. The pudding makes a glaze so the fruit does not turn dark, even after several days.
This can be made with regular Jell-O pudding if you aren't watching your sugar.
Very good. This is excellent for picnics and large crowds.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles to desired tenderness; set aside and drain.
Mix the cream cheese, Parmesan, milk, butter and garlic together until smooth and creamy.
Add noodles or pour sauce over noodles in bowl.

title: chocolate crunch candy
directions: Combine powdered milk and cocoa in blender, blending to a fine powder.
Stir in fructose and water.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Slightly crush the chow mein noodles and fold them into the chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 30 pieces at 11 calories per piece.

title: potato cheese chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in saucepan.
Remove bacon and drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion to drippings and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add cheese, stirring, until melted (8 1/2 cups).

title: corn maque choux(cajun cream corn)
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, combine the corn, margarine, bell pepper, salt and red pepper. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add the sugar and milk and cook for 16 minutes or until the corn is tender.

title: eggless baby cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
In a small saucepan, combine the juice concentrate, dried fruits, margarine and cinnamon.
Simmer over low heat until the margarine melts.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flours, wheat germ and baking powder.
Slowly add the fruit mixture and stir just until mixed.
Coat an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with vegetable spray and pour in the batter.
Bake about 30 minutes, until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and then cut into 16 squares. For future use, wrap pieces individually and store in the freezer in airtight container.
Babies love to gum small pieces of this chewy cake.

title: newcomer cookies
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix and add to first mixture the buttermilk and baking soda.
Next, add flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Put small amount of batter on a greased cookie sheet. It will be runny, but should round up and raise when baked. If not, add a little more flour to the batter.
Check batter by baking one cookie.
Continue this process until cookie rounds up and raises nicely.
Bake at 450°.
Tops can be sprinkled with colored sugar before baking.
Cookies can be frosted with favorite flavor after cookies cool.
Yield:
6 to 8 dozen.

title: florentine rondelles
directions: Cook the spinach according to package directions.
Combine it with the bread crumbs, onion, cheese, herbs and spices.
Add the eggs and butter.
Mix well with your hands.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Freeze on a cookie sheet.
Pack into bags for storage. Keep frozen until ready to serve.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Complement with a cocktail.

title: corn pudding(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix sugar and flour; stir into melted butter.
Stir in milk, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in corn.
Pour mixture into 2-quart buttered casserole or two 1-quart baking dishes.
(I usually make it in two dishes and freeze one for later.)
Bake in oven until top is golden brown and center is set, about 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring with the cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs to the cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add vinegar and baking soda with a spoon.
Bake in greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add meat and brown slightly. Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all but the soda and corn.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Put the popped corn into a brown paper bag.
Pour the syrup over the corn and shake. Microwave in bag for 1 minute.
Shake and pour into a pan to cool.

title: rich corn bread
directions: Melt the butter in iron skillet; let it get real hot.
Add corn bread mixture.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into 6 wedges.
Remove carefully with a metal spatula, scraping bottom to get crust.
Serve hot.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: easy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring syrup and sugar to a boil. Put in	9 x 13-inch
pan
and
add
peanut
butter
and
Rice Krispies; mix together.
Scatter large package chocolate chips over top;
turn off oven. Leave in oven until chips melt.
Use back of spoon to spread chips evenly. Cool; cut into bars.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Shred cabbage; place in large pan with butter in oven.
Stir occasionally, letting cabbage brown.
Boil noodles until done; drain and stir into browned cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Ready to serve.
Great with corned beef and more.

title: beer bread
directions: Blend and put into 3 small loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add the flavorings and egg yolk. Add the flour by hand. The hardest part, spread 1/4-inch thick on a large cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then with sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until eggs are set.
Can be held nicely in a warm oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into loaf pan, greased.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Blend all ingredients (hot potatoes) with mixer.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: north carolina meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well. Pour into bottle and refrigerate. Shake well before using.

title: best-ever cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, water and oil; blend well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour batter into a well-greased Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.

title: pull apart microwave rolls
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch quiche pan.
This will grease the pan, then pour butter in pitcher.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for glaze. Cut biscuits into quarters.
Put 1 can of cut up biscuits in pan. Pour 1/2 of the melted butter over the top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Repeat the layers, ending with sugar on top. Bake in microwave for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Top with glaze.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir together cheese and chili.
Microwave at Medium-high until melted.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugars together; add eggs, butter and vanilla.
Gradually add in flour, salt and soda.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut out cookies using round cookie cutter or if you don't have a round cutter a kitchen glass will work fine (dip in flour first).
Press M&M's lightly on top of each cookie, careful not to disturb round shape. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until sides are lightly brown.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix eggs, mayo, milk, and flour.
Then add onions, spinach and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Follow spinach directions on package.
Must drain well.
Can add bacon bits or mushrooms.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Lay out 1/2 bread cubes in a 13-inch square baking dish. Spread out all cream cheese cubes over bread.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Add to beaten eggs the milk, maple flavor and sugar. Carefully pour over bread and cream cheese.
Cover; let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Serve with warmed maple syrup, breakfast beverage and/or meat of your choice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot meat or vegetables in boiling stew (do not drop directly into liquid).
Cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 to 10 dumplings.

title: curry dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all the ingredients and stir until blended.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
In ovenproof skillet or baking pan, melt butter or margarine and garlic salt.
Add bread cubes; toss to coat.
Place in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until croutons are quite dry and crispy.
Refrigerate in tightly covered jar until needed.
Yields 3 cups.

title: muffuletta(new orleans sandwich)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Cut bread in half.
Remove center from top and bottom.
Drizzle some oil on bread.
Fill with layers of meat and cheese.
Put olive salad on top.
Cover with bread top.
Place in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken, then remove from skillet.
Sprinkle flour into fat; stir constantly until mixture turns light brown (don't burn).
Return chicken, sausage, onions, green pepper, tomatoes and garlic.
Cook, stirring gently, for 10 minutes.
Stir in water, thyme, salt and rice.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley and green onions and simmer 5 minutes longer or until rice is tender.

title: burritos
directions: Crumble, stir and fry sausage until done.
Drain excess grease.
Add beans and cheese.
Mix grated onions.
Lay flour tortillas in large skillet on low fire; warm on both sides.
Place large tablespoon bean mixture in middle, top with large tablespoon onion and roll up.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: bernice's cake
directions: Combine butter, egg and cake mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine the cream cheese, eggs, brown sugar and powdered sugar.
Beat smooth.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after removing from oven.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Line a 12 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Put graham crackers on foil.
Sprinkle pecans on crackers.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Add potatoes to water and salt in saucepan; mix.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and boil until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chuck steak au vin
directions: Place steak on foil.
Put over steak the sliced onion, Worcestershire sauce, powdered beef bouillon and 1/4 to 1/2 cup sweet vermouth.
Close foil around steak, folding the ends so the liquid won't escape.
Roast in slow oven (300°) for 4 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and mix; roll in finely chopped pecans and chill.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: date bars
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, sugar and water.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thick.
Stir in nuts, if desired.

title: banana pudding(microwave)
directions: Put in microwave and cook until thick.
Pour over banana and vanilla wafers.

title: lois campbell's butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix oil, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
While warm, cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix gelatin into boiling water until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients except carrot.
Chill until mixture is slightly thick.
Shred carrot.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 4-cup mold or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill until set.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make one big well and two small wells in mixture.
Put oil in large well and vanilla and vinegar in the small ones.
Pour water over top of all of this.
Mix only until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Add all ingredients to large soup pot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover. Cook for 1 hour.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
While warm, punch holes in cake.
Cover with condensed milk.
Make sure milk soaks in holes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Beat candy bar or break into small pieces.
Sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and cook face down in 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn squash over.
Sprinkle with a little salt. Combine pineapple, apple and brown sugar.
Fill squash.
Dot with butter.
Return to oven.
Bake for 30 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl and set aside.
Cook bacon in skillet on medium heat to desired crispness.
Remove bacon from skillet and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and cream cheese in 2 cups of hot water. Add to gelatin, dissolved in 1 1/2 cups of hot water.
Add pineapple (drained well) and nuts.
Refrigerate.
(You may also use strawberry gelatin!!)

title: party mix
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt margarine with sauces and salt.
In large pan mix Chex, nuts and pretzels.
Add liquids; stir and place in 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: turtle cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips until smooth.
Mix pecans with chocolate and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Melt 1/2 cup caramels and pour on top on pecans and chocolate mixture.

title: dixie celery casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, place celery, salt and water to cover. Cook 8 minutes on high heat; drain.
In small mixing bowl, blend chicken soup with milk, tabasco and water chestnuts.
Butter an 8-inch casserole.
Sprinkle celery over bottom.
Cover with soup mixture.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan.
Blend with almonds and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Mix in salt, pepper, cheese and mushroom soup.
Put in casserole and put broken potato chips or bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pink lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend milk and lemonade well.
Add Cool Whip, blending well. Pour into the pie crust and chill several hours.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut beef in thin slices.
Combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce with sugar, ginger and garlic.
Stir in beef. Cut up broccoli.
Combine remaining cornstarch and soy sauce with 1 cup of water, then set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in wok or large skillet on high heat.
Add meat, then add remaining oil to wok, then add broccoli, onion and carrots.
Stir-fry for 4 minutes until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Then add soy sauce mixture; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mash bananas in a large bowl, add flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and egg.
Melt butter in microwave, add it to bowl and stir until just blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 70 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower, broccoli florets and green peppers into bite-size pieces. Add Ranch dressing and stir. Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together.
Put sugar and oil together in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs gradually then vanilla.
Add flour mixture all at once and beat well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls, roll in sugar and place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Flatten with a fork and sprinkle again with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove to cooling trays.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: quick onion burgers
directions: Mix beef and soup mix; shape into 6 patties.
In skillet, cook patties until done.
Serve on buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine in saucepan brown sugar, Karo and butter.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn in large baking dish (or 2 long pans) and bake at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: meat lover's cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in large skillet.
Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake per directions.
When cake cools, poke with fork all over cake.
Bring pineapple and juice and 1/2 cup sugar to a boil. Let cool, then pour over cooled cake.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Mix 1 package of vanilla pudding and spread over bananas.
Then sprinkle with coconut.
Then spread on Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: mediterranean saute
directions: Saute peppers, zucchini, onions and oregano in margarine. Stir in tomatoes.
Continue cooking 1 minute.
Remove from heat; top with cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer until thick.
Use to marinate meat for barbecue.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions. Drain and set aside. Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat. Beat 1 egg, then add 2 to 3 teaspoons of hot butter mixture to the egg. Stir well and pour back into the butter mixture and return to medium heat for about 1 minute. Stir in 1 cup of cheese until smooth. Lightly grease a 3-quart casserole dish and layer macaroni and cheese, ending with a layer of cheese sauce. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Top with remaining shredded cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 10 more minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 3/4 stick oleo and cracker crumbs and place in large baking dish.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo, mix with cracker crumbs and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350°.
When casserole bubbles it is done.

title: garlic parmesan pasta
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add basil, lemon juice and garlic powder with parsley and seasoned salt.
Blend well; add fettuccine, broccoli, walnuts and Parmesan cheese to coat.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until serving time.
Makes a large bowl full.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: little hamburger patties with onion and gravy
directions: Combine hamburger and onion. Make little patties about the size of silver dollars. Dip in flour to coat. Set aside. In medium-hot skillet, melt 2 to 3 tablespoons shortening. Add patties and fry until fully cooked. Mix flour and warm water in airtight container. Shake until flour is dissolved. Add additional water to hot grease, then add flour/water mixture and stir until you have gravy. Pour gravy over patties and serve.

title: snakebite's chicken #1
directions: Make enough for two.
Mix rice, water, soup and soup mix in a bowl.
Place chicken or pork chops in deep baking dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Cover.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add soups, corn, sour cream, chopped pimento, salt, Accent and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft.
Beat in sugar and prepared Dream Whip.
Spread on bottom and sides of pie shell; chill.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain syrup from strawberries and add to jello.
Chill jello until thickened.
Fold in strawberries and put into crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: hamburger turnovers
directions: Brown beef
and
onion.
Let
cool
and drain.
Stir in cheese, egg, salt and chili powder; mix well.
Use rolling pin and roll
out each individual crescent roll as large as possible. Spoon
filling
into crescent roll and fold over, making into a turnover.
Place
on
greased baking sheet and bake at 425° until crust is golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: beef-bacon chicken
directions: Wrap dried beef around breasts, then wrap bacon around breasts and beef, holding with a toothpick.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: strawberry mousse pie
directions: Put the cold water in a saucepan; sprinkle gelatin on top and let stand a minute to soften. Then stir over low heat until dissolved. Remove from heat.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, mustard and mayo.
Coat in corn flakes.
Place on "Pam" coated pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Doubles easily!

title: deluxe pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in electric frypan (325°) on both sides. Wash and slice potatoes and place on top of chops.
Slice onion and place on top of potatoes and top with cooked carrot slices. Pour tomato soup or mushroom soup over all.
Add can of water. Turn down temperature of frypan and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. You complete meal is ready when vegetables can be easily pierced with a fork.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onion and drain.
Mix together with all but last 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Roll in flour.
Mix eggs and milk. Dip balls in this mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
French fry. They are great.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line pan with foil.
Cut dough in 8 one-inch slices and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes and cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over dough.
Arrange fruit over pizza.
Mix orange marmalade and water.
Dribble over fruit.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of quiche dish.
Mix onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Pour taco sauce on top to cover.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving. Sprinkle with cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: vinegar noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Cool.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients.
Add to noodles.
Mix and chill.

title: strawberry pie syrup
directions: Cook sugar and 1 cup of water together until syrupy.
Take cornstarch, a little water, Jell-O and red food coloring, add to thicken syrup.
Let cool and add berries.

title: not-so-sloppy joes
directions: Wash and chop the green onions.
Put the hamburger meat in the frying pan.
Add the chopped up onions and cook over low heat until brown; drain fat.
Add the other ingredients (except the hamburger buns) and simmer for a few minutes.
Spoon onto your hamburger buns and serve.

title: hash brown casserole i
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Boil chicken with spices until done and remove from broth and save broth.
When chicken is cool enough to handle, remove meat, discarding skin and bones.
Boil noodles according to package directions in leftover broth until done.
May have to add more water to broth.
Drain and leave a little broth in bottom of pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup to hot noodles and stir, add onion, rotel tomatoes, chicken, and mushrooms if you desire.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2 dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with parmesan cheese on top if desired.
Add garlic bread and a salad for a delicious meal.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Use 1/2 of mixture to stuff peppers.
Use other 1/2 over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix. Then add chocolate chips and coconut. Mix well. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage and cheese to stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes for easier mixing.
Mix sausage, cheese and paprika; add Bisquick and shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 100 balls.
May be frozen.

title: crock-pot boliche
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
Make a lengthwise cut through center of roast.
Stuff with sausage.
Pierce meat and insert garlic throughout roast.

title: pickled beets(rodbeter)
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, juice from beets, salt and pepper in stainless steel 2-quart saucepan.
Add a few cloves tied in cloth bag.
Bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, place beets in glass, stainless steel or enamel bowl.
Pour hot marinade over beets.
Let cool, uncovered.
When mixture is room temperature, cover bowl.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add rest of ingredients. Pour in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: soy and sesame pork tenderloin
directions: Put pork tenderloin in a large Ziploc plastic bag.
Make marinade by combining remaining ingredients (except sesame seeds). Pour marinade over pork.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or longer, turning several times.
Remove pork from marinade.
Put marinade in a small saucepan; set aside.
Place pork on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Add enough water to roasting pan to cover bottom of pan, but not touch pork.
Place pan in a preheated 450° oven and roast pork 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°; sprinkle each tenderloin with about 1/2 teaspoon sesame seeds and roast until pork reaches an internal temperature of 170°, about 35 minutes more.
Let pork rest 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Meanwhile, bring marinade to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Cut pork and pork marinade over pork.
Serves 4.

title: his majesty's special
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken.
Place skin side up in baking dish. Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve over potatoes, noodles or rice.

title: broccoli beef pie
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Brown beef in skillet; crumble and drain off drippings.
Stir in mushrooms, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and onion.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 9 in. unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat in oven to 350 degrees.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Put margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Cook on low heat 2 minutes.
Add milk and boil constantly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups sifted powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs one at a time and beat well; add vinegar and vanilla, beat in coconut. Pour in pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked pears
directions: Drain about half of the juice from pear halves.
Put pears in baking dish.
Save 1/2 cup juice.
Dissolve cinnamon in juice. Mix together the brown sugar, sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon mixture.
Pour over pears.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: children's play dough(children's recipe)
directions: 1/4 cup sugar = 1 teaspoon Sweet 'N Low

title: pastafazool
directions: Cook soup beans until done.
Saute one medium onion in butter. Season with 2 to 4 slices of thick chopped ham.
Add one large can tomato sauce.
Add one large can of chicken broth; cook 20 minutes. Add one cup of cooked elbow macaroni when ready to serve.

title: imperial fruit salad freeze
directions: Mash bananas gently with fork.
Blend in other ingredients. Stir well and freeze in sherbet dishes or glass 9-inch pie plate. Cut in wedges to serve.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 5 half slices of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally after 1/2 hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll balls of salmon in cracker crumbs. Heat skillet filled with 1/4-inch Crisco.
Fry until golden brown on low to medium heat.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic in large salad bowl.
Beat in mustard, Italian dressing and parsley.
Add lettuce and toss lightly covering leaves with dressing.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese; toss lightly. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; sift next 4 ingredients together. Combine dry ingredients with pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Beat well until smooth, then add chopped dates that have been sprinkled with flour.
Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans or loaf pan.
Fill half full and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: nacho style bean bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, corn, tomatoes, olives, onion and spices.
On bottom of a 11 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan, place 2 cups crushed tortilla chips.
Top with bean mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 2 cups of chips over beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool, then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: banana fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits.
Toss lightly with sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take chicken off the bone.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix stuffing and soup.
Cook in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream of cauliflower or broccoli soup
directions: Prepare cauliflower (whole 20 to 25 minutes, flowerets 10 to 12 minutes); drain.
Heat 2 cups water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan. Add cauliflower, celery, onion and lemon juice.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes; do not drain.
Press cauliflower mixture through food mill or place in blender until uniform consistency.
Heat margarine in 3 quart saucepan (low) until melted.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in cauliflower mixture, instant bouillon, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat just to boiling.
Stir in cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve with grated cheese if desired.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Mix ingredients, except cornflakes, nuts and powdered sugar. Roll into balls about the size of an egg.
Roll in crushed corn flakes and chopped nuts to coat.
Drop potato balls into deep, hot fat and fry until rich brown color.
Remove from deep fat and roll in powdered sugar.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain the first 8 ingredients and place in dish.
Bring the vinegar, sugar, oil and salt and pepper to a boil. Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: turtle cake
directions: Bake cake as on box directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan, greased and lightly floured.
When cake comes out of oven, immediately punch holes all over cake.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk all over the top evenly, then pour the jar of caramel topping over top of cake.
Allow to set awhile to soak in the toppings. Can top with Cool Whip.
Serve plain or delicious with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in hot oil in large skillet until soft.
Add chicken, tomato sauce, tomatoes, salsa, garlic powder and parsley; stir well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and place 4 tortillas in bottom.
Spread 1/3 of the chicken on top.
Layer 1/3 of the cheese, then 1/3 olives.
Repeat twice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until cheese is light brown and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Make jello. Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Allow the marshmallows and cheese to melt.
Add the rest of the ingredients. After cooling a few minutes, add 2 cups cold water.
Stir just before it sets.

title: holiday cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together good.
Form 2 balls.
Roll in finely chopped pecans until ball is covered.
Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: louisiana chicken sauce piquante
directions: Measure cooking oil and pour into large cast-iron pot.
Cut chickens into serving size pieces and season with salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Brown in cooking oil.
Remove chicken from pot and place in pan.

title: flat dumplings for chicken and dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening as for pie dough.
Beat egg and milk; add to flour. Form into a ball.
Pinch off small pieces and roll very thin. Success of dumplings is the thinness.
Cut in 2-inch squares. Cook 20 minutes in hot broth.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Stir all together in mixing bowl.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: siberian pelmeni(poached pastries)
directions: Sift the flour onto the dough board.
Make a hollow in the center of the flour.
Break in the egg; add milk or water and salt.
Knead into a heavy dough; cover and set aside for half an hour.
Roll the dough thin and cut 2 to 2 1/2-inch rounds.
Put a ball of filling (about the size of a small walnut) on one half of the round and fold over making a half moon.
Pinch the edges, draw
the two points together making a little purse.

title: hot cocoa mix(great gift for friends at christmas!)
directions: Mix together and sift.
Store in jars.
Fill cup half full of mix and add boiling water.

title: salmon loaf with dill sauce
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix salmon, milk, bread crumbs and eggs. Add onion, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well, but do not overmix.
Place into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Prepare Dill Sauce (recipe follows).

title: german cabbage slaw
directions: Place cabbage, onion and peppers in earthenware.
Pour 1 cup sugar over vegetables and let set 20 minutes.
Heat to boiling 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Store in glass jars.
Will keep a month.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Mix remaining ingredients and fill peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake another 30 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Grease four individual 8 to 10 ounce broiler-safe baking dishes.
In a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of butter over moderate heat.
Pour the butter into a small bowl.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Set the buttered crumbs aside.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cube the chicken breast.

title: skillet meal delight
directions: Heat diced bacon, ground meat and chopped onion in skillet on high temperature.
Switch to medium heating until slightly brown. Add remaining ingredients in order given.
When steaming, turn to low heat.
Cook about 35 minutes covered tightly.

title: alysa's orange and onion salad
directions: Alternate orange slices and onion slices attractively in a serving dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients well and drizzle over salad.
Serve immediately on a bed of salad greens, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: In casserole dish, place the pork chops side by side.
Put 2 tablespoons rice on top of pork chop.
Next, put sliced garlic and spoon 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce on top.
Cover with large slices of onion and sprinkle with plenty of salt and pepper.
Pour water over chops until it is one inch above everything.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with a green salad.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onion and saute, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until limp.
Add the potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add the stock, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the vegetables, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pork chops with sauerkraut
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion tender. Mix with sauerkraut, apples and pepper.
Arrange pork chops over sauerkraut in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° until pork is done.
Uncover and let chops brown some.

title: janet's fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and use 2 cups of the fruit juice for pudding. Mix and use the same day as prepared.

title: meatball submarine sandwich
directions: Slice roll in half, lengthways.
Heat meatballs and tomato sauce in microwave until warm.
Spread meatball and tomato mixture over bottom half of roll.
Top with mozzarella cheese.
Broil this and the top half of roll in toaster oven or regular oven until cheese is melted.
Combine and eat.

title: carrot salad
directions: In small bowl, with electric mixer on high, beat cream until stiff peaks form; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; toss to blend.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve immediately or cover and chill to serve later.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Mix broccoli and onions.
Beat eggs, mayonnaise and mushroom soup until smooth.
Layer broccoli mix and cheese/cracker crumbs on top.
Pour mushroom soup mix over all and top with cheese/cracker crumbs and dot top with butter.
Bake in oven at about 350° for about an hour until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together and microwave on Full for 2 minutes and refrigerate.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, dill, salt and pepper. Add macaroni, cucumber, tomato and onion.
Toss to coat well. Cover and chill.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery; cook for a few minutes.
Blend together remaining ingredients, reserving a few noodles for the top.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour as for pie crust.
Add pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cheese until light and fluffy; fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare lemon pudding according to package, using 3 cups milk; spoon over cheese layer.
Top with whipped cream. Chill for several hours or overnight.
(Other flavored puddings may be substituted.)

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a medium saucepan; blend well.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour hot filling into bowl.
Cover with wax paper and chill.
Whip chilled mixture until creamy; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Spoon whipped cream around edge of shell.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Boil whole chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Add 2 or 3 chicken bouillon cubes to broth for extra flavor.
Debone chicken and put meat back in broth.
Cook on medium heat while preparing dumplings.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetarian "meat" loaf
directions: Gently mix
and
place in greased loaf pan.
No salt is needed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix and freeze in gallon freezer until firm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions; drain and cool.
In a large bowl, mix together cool macaroni, celery, onion, pimiento, chicken chunks, pickle relish, and American cheese cubes.
Stir together the mayonnaise and cream and pour over the chicken mixture; mix well.
Place shredded lettuce on plates and top with chicken mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: golfer's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Lay chicken pieces in broiler pan.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° in the oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 pecans and all other ingredients.
Shape into balls and refrigerate several hours.
Roll cheese balls in remaining chopped pecans.

title: heleyne's favorite fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Remove from heat; add milk, salt, vanilla and nuts or coconut.
Stir until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly into waxed paper-lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours, until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board and peel off waxed paper.
Cut into squares.
Tightly cover. Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage and drain.
Add cheese, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Continue to cook until cheese is melted.
Put mixture on bread slices and put under broiler for about 1 minute.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread using 2 cups meal according to directions on cornmeal package.
Using large bowl, layer cornbread, bacon, onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sweet pickles.
Make as many layers as possible.
Combine mayonnaise, pickle juice and sugar.
Blend well and drizzle over salad.
Toss lightly before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: zucchini cake(makes a large cake)
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs, soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and beat more.
Add flour and beat more.
Be sure it is beaten well.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in blender 2 or 3 seconds or mix in large jar and shake well.
Should dressing get too thick, add some water.
Will keep 3 or 4 weeks.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix macaroni with rest of ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: garlic lemon pasta
directions: In a small skillet, cook garlic in oil until golden. (Do not brown garlic; it will be bitter.) Add lemon juice, pepper and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves. Toss with hot pasta, Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: cheesy garlic biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cheese and garlic; mix well, coating all the cheese.
Add Crisco shortening in small lumps, blending with fork until crumbly.
Add milk, a spoonful at a time, while mixing with fork.
You may not need all the milk.
Press dough out on floured surface.
Make biscuits as thick or thin as you like, also as big or little as you like, depending on your biscuit cutter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pilgrim punch
directions: Combine juices in a large pitcher or punch bowl.
Add sugar and stir well to dissolve.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Add ice cubes and ginger ale just before serving. Put lemon slice on glass.

title: peanut butter dreams
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill.
Melt chocolate pieces.
Spread over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: texas hash
directions: Take potatoes and dice into small pieces.
Then fry. Meanwhile, brown ground meat separately; then drain excess fluid from meat.
Combine potatoes and meat; then saute chopped jalapenos and onions in a small amount of butter.
Scramble eggs. Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Deep Fry chicken wings for about 12 minutes or until cooked and crispy; drain.
In large bowl, combine Franks Redhot sauce and butter.
Toss wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with blue cheese salad dressing and celery sticks.

title: texas cake
directions: Boil butter, cocoa and water.
(Microwave is easiest.)
Pour this into flour, sugar and salt.
Beat together eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour into flour mixture and mix well.
Place in greased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet with rims.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Ice cake while hot.

title: low-fat spinach and chestnut dip
directions: Squeeze excess liquid from the spinach.
In a large bowl, stir together the yogurt, mayonnaise and soup mix.
Then stir in the spinach, water chestnuts and onion.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator about 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve with cut-up fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: In
a
10-inch
skillet, melt butter.
Stir in nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar melts and nuts brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Decorate tops of cookies with M&M's candies or any other decorating candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
(Miss Harris cooked for 7 or 8 minutes.)
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mother's lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco.
Cream well.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Divide evenly into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Lemon Cheese Frosting.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Cut margarine and place on bottom of baking dish.
Pour batter over margarine.
Cover batter with can of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with hand mixer.
Slice several apples and dip.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Put butter in large saucepan and melt over low heat.
Then slowly add your corn flakes and peanut butter. Mix until all flakes are covered.
For variations, you can also add almonds, coconut, chocolate chips, wheat germ, etc.
Just about anything will do to make this basic recipe into something anyone would like.
After mixing, put onto plate.
Press out and cool, then cut and enjoy.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients except flour.
Stir in flour just to mix.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar before removing from pan.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and fine nuts to make like pie crust and pat in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread over crust.
Beat pudding and milk until smooth and thick. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In 1-quart measuring cup, melt butter in microwave; blend in flour and salt. Stir in milk. Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes. Stir after 4 minutes. Layer half of potatoes in casserole; sprinkle with onion and sauce. Repeat layers; cover. Microwave on High for 17 to 18 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and paprika if desired. Ovens vary; may need to bake longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and pumpkin.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture and blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese(baked)
directions: Beat
eggs, salt, pepper and milk together.
Put a layer of cooked macaroni in greased 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole.
Add layer of
grated
cheese, margarine and crushed cracker.
Pour half
of milk over top.
Put another layer of macaroni, margarine,
cheese and crushed cracker.
Add rest of milk.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine sugars and shortening; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients into creamed sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell.
In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup of sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thick.
Add a little mixture to egg yolks.
Return all to hot mixture.
Cook for about 2 minutes.
Put in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell until it cools a little.
Stir 1/4 cup of sugar in can of cherries and put on top of pie.

title: my grandmother's pumpkin pie
directions: Sift sugar with flour.
Add pumpkin, nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Salt to taste.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Stir in evaporated and fresh milk.
Add more sugar, to taste.
Add vanilla. Pour into uncooked shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 325° for 45 minutes.
Thick filling takes about an hour.
Pie is done when knife blade used to test comes out clean.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to firm ball stage or until mixture forms a firm ball which does not flatten when dropped in cold water.
Just before it reaches the ball stage, beat the egg whites until stiff.

title: breakfast cereal
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add margarine and water to moisten. Spread in well-greased cookie sheet. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with soup, mushrooms and cheese. Top with onion rings. Bake at 200° until bubbly.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Put butter in cold skillet.
Turn heat to low and melt.
Add sugar and egg, stirring well to mix egg in before it starts to scramble.
When all mixed, add dates and turn heat to medium. Stir constantly while cooking, mashing dates.
Cook about 8 minutes.
Do not overcook or it will scorch. This stuff is going to be hot.
Pour out onto a buttered cookie sheet and spread a little.
Butter hands and roll mixture into small balls. Try not to make them too large.
Then roll them in powdered sugar.
When all have been rolled, I go back and roll them again.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook in boiling water with skins on until tender.
When cool, slice potatoes.
Season with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Keep warm.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: *Put small amounts into blender until it turns to powder. Measure first, then blend.

title: lucy's breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage.
Shred cheese and put in pie crust.
Put sausage on top of cheese.
Mix milk and eggs together and pour over cheese and sausage.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin crumb pie
directions: Bring raisins, sugar and 1 cup water to a full boil.
Mix water, flour and eggs; beat until smooth.
Add to the cooked raisin mixture while still boiling to thicken.
Fill unbaked pie shells with mixture and add Crumb Topping.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Let boil hard for 1 minutes.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana fritters
directions: Peel and cut the bananas into 1/2-inch slices.
Sprinkle with the sugar and orange juice. Leave for 20 minutes.

title: microwave basic meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion, crumbs, egg, ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Mold into a rounded flat loaf in 9-inch pie plate (Pyrex).
Spread ketchup evenly over top of loaf.
Insert temperature probe and cover with plastic, arranging loosely around probe.

title: flavorful beef stir-fry
directions: In a bowl, combine cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, wine and apple juice or water until smooth. Add beef and toss to coat; set aside.

title: ham balls
directions: Blend cheese and ham.
Refrigerate until easy to handle.
Shape into small balls, approximately 30 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate long enough to firm up.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend together 2 eggs, sugar, chopped apples, oil and vanilla.

title: parmesan cheese substitute
directions: Put
all ingredients in a dry blender.
Mix until seeds are milled and ingredients are combined.
Store in refrigerator. Keeps for months.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Melt 2/3 cup margarine and add to (all but 1/3 cup) vanilla wafer crumbs.
Press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate squares in microwave and set aside. Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat egg yolks, then add chocolate mixture, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg whites. Cook this mixture until it begins to boil. Boil 1 to 2 minutes. Spread this over crust and freeze for 10 to 20 minutes.
Add softened ice cream and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup wafer crumbs and freeze.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, peel and grate.
Heat 1/2 cup butter with soup.
Blend sour cream, onion and cheese into soup.
Add to potatoes and place into buttered casserole.
Mix corn flakes with remaining butter and sprinkle on top.

title: banana boat
directions: Peel
back
a
section of the banana peel (don't remove it). Cut a wedge along the length of the banana (about 1/4 of the banana).
Eat
the wedge.
Put some chocolate chips in the cavity with
some	marshmallows.
Replace	the
peel over the banana and wrap
and
seal
well in foil.
Cook on coals for 7 minutes.
Let cool before eating.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9-inch square baking pan. In medium bowl, combine 1 cup flour, oats, butter and brown sugar until crumbly. Press into baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: diet cake
directions: Put raisins in water; cook until dry.
Add oil, eggs, sweetener and applesauce, then flour and spices.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt together all the chips and stir in the peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let them stand until hardened.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix hamburger, onions, salt, Worcestershire sauce, and pepper together.
Form into small balls, about an inch in diameter.
Roll in flour and brown in shortening.
When brown on all sides, add the mushroom soup and 3/4 can of water; simmer for 30 minutes.
In another saucepan, cook potatoes, carrots and peas until tender. When tender, mix with meat mixture and place in a large, shallow dish.
Top with biscuit and bake until biscuits are brown.
You can sprinkle some cheese over the top when still hot if you like.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter and mix with cookies.
Press into pan.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Put 1 cup of this over cookies.
Beat milk with pudding and pour over other two layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Remove stems.
Insert a wooden skewer into stem of each apple.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and dash of salt.
Mix well.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Dip each apple into caramel.
Turn to coat.
Set on buttered baking sheet.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes (test for doneness).

title: marbled chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Blend together.
Add sugar, 2 eggs and flour.
Beat until smooth.
With brownie mix, use 1/3 cup oil.
Add 2 tablespoons water and 3 eggs.
Mix by hand.
Pour 1/2 of brownie mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all of cream cheese mix over this.
Spoon remaining brownie mix on top and marble with knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.
tags: Duncan Hines family size brownie mix

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the cream cheese and sugar; blend well.
Add cocoa; blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Add whipping cream; blend well.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill several hours. Garnish with pie filling.

title: sausage sandwich
directions: In a 9 x 13 baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam, unroll one tube of crescent rolls (you will have to encourage it to fit).

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix jello and 1 cup boiling water, then cool.
Mix crackers, melted margarine and sugar together and press into large pan (10 x 14 x 2-inch).
Save some crumbs for the topping.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together and cream well.
Whip chilled milk and add lemon jello, then add cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan and chill 12 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar. Beat well. Add salt and vanilla. Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well after each. Add cake flour; mix well. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 275° and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Brown the meat and onion.
Drain off any grease.
Place meat and onion in a large, thick-bottomed pot or a crock-pot.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cook slowly for at least 4 hours, covered.
Remove bay leaves and garlic before serving. Serve on a bed of spaghetti and top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: sour creamed walnuts
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together until it forms a soft ball. Stir in nuts.
Spread on foil to cool.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In another container, mix flour and sugar.
Put 1/2 yeast mixture in flour mixture.
Add egg, shortening and rest of yeast mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Cover. Let rise 30 minutes.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill the tins half full.
Let this rise 30 minutes, covered.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut cream cheese easter eggs
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Add flour and powdered sugar; add coconut.
Mix well.
Shape into eggs.
Chill overnight on wax paper.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar for 1 minute.
Cool and pour over rest of ingredients.

title: orange strawberry juice froth
directions: In blender, process ingredients for about 20 seconds or until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately.

title: pasta with virgin broccoli
directions: Trim tough ends of broccoli and peel stalks.
Quarter broccoli lengthwise and cut into 2-inch long pieces.
Cook broccoli in big pan of salted, boiling water.
When broccoli is just tender, lift out of water with strainer or slotted spoon, letting excess water drain back into pan.

title: barbeque turkey drumsticks
directions: In small saucepan combine all ingredients except turkey. Simmer 15-20 minutes over low heat.
Arrange turkey in foil lined roasting pan.
Pour sauce over turkey.
Cover and marinate 2 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the eggs well.
Add the pumpkin pie filling and oil.
Gradually add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients; mix well.
Put in greased and floured pans.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split muffins and place halves with cut side up on a baking sheet.
Combine tomato sauce and oregano in a bowl.
Coat muffins with tomato sauce mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil until cheese is bubbly and serve warm.

title: onion supper bread
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Prepare muffin mix according to package.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with cooked onion.
Mix sour cream and cheese; spoon over top.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Cream margarine; blend in sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Spread into greased 8 x 12-inch utility dish.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in 4 cup measure at Medium for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are soft.
Stir until smooth.
Spread over oat mixture.
Refrigerate until quite chilled.
Cut into bars.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Blend butter, cheese spread, mayonnaise, garlic salt and crab meat and spread on muffins.
Freeze on cookie sheet until hard. Cut into quarters.
